INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2004, 'zfP2fK', '12th Of Never', 5.5, 'Tropically Hoppy. Light, yet Full-Bodied. Bright and Citrusy. Word.\r\nThe magical, mystical 12th of Never is a blend of Old and New School hops that play bright citrus, rich coconut, and papaya-esque flavors, all on a solid stage of English puffed wheat. Tropically hoppy. Light, yet full-bodied. Bright and citrusy. The 12th of Never Ale is everything we’ve learned about making hop-forward beer expressed in a moderate voice.  Pale, cold, slightly alcoholic and bitter.  It’s all we know.\r\n\r\nThese 12oz mini-kegs (AKA cans) are an exciting new option for us, and we are stoopid stoked at the opportunity for y\'all to take us to all those new, nelophobic locations…', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-zfP2fK-+1.Lagunitas-12th-of-Never-Featured.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2005, 'UJGpVS', '16 So Fine Red Wheat Wine', 11, 'For our super heady 16 year anniversary beer we stepped on the gas and headed down the road less traveled! Our b-day present to ourselves was a racy Red Wheat Wine. The brew rips down the road at 11% ABV fueld by a 45% wheat bomb with an after burner hop shot of Amarillo, Willamette, Nelson Sauvignon, and US Goldings that pushes this baby to the limit of sensory overload. Get in. Sit down. Hold on. Shut up.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-UJGpVS-+1.sweetwater_16.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2006, 'Yd8G8r', '18th Anniversary Belgian Tripel', 10, 'This brilliant Belgian Tripel showcases the best of our brewers as we bring to life 18 years of passion for beer and strive to crate the most interesting beers possible. This tripel leads with complex citrus aromas that are complimented by a strong undertow of spicy hop character. Ardennes yeast brings forward fruity esters as the Belgian candy sugar added in fermentation softens the body while leading to a vigorous ABV in the finished beer.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Yd8G8r-+1.sweetwater-belgian-tripel-anniversary-ale.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2007, 'iJ329Y', '19 - Golden Belgian Style Ale', 7, 'This Golden Belgian Style Ale matured for over a year on brett in Cabernet and Merlot barrels, then was blended with a bright, citrusy hop-forward Belgian style IPA. Four plus two equals seven here, as the finished product is bigger than the sum of its parts. The art of this crafted cuvee is in the hop profile with a Belgian style nose up front, followed by woody undertones and a complex finish. After 19 years we’re still all about brewing great beer, supporting the communities who drink it and having a kick ass time along the way.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-iJ329Y-+1.ECLP5818_2019_RussianRiver_HoppyBelgian_Collab_Label_M1_19SE11_TRIM-1600x800.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2008, 'O78ldO', '1904 American Red Lager', 5, '1904 American Red Lager is a special beer that goes by many names depending on which restaurant you visit!', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-O78ldO-+1.red-rock-sets-25-55.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2009, 'qGDeH1', '2 x 4', 8.7, '40% Belgian-style Quad Ale aged in brandy barrels with dates and currants added, 60% Belgian-style Dubbel Ale.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-qGDeH1-+1.Melvin-2x4-SellSheet.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2010, 'MgdJep', '200th Anniversary Export Stout', 6, 'Toffee caramel with subtle chocolate notes. Complex and very smooth with a balance of roasted malt and sweet chocolate.', 'Guinness', 'Dublin', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-MgdJep-+1.200th_anniversary_stout_product_image_mobile.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2011, 'ISTT06', '2017 Beer Camp', 6.5, 'At Beer Camp, no beer style is off limits, so we jumped at the idea of doing a Golden IPA using wheat malt for a light, dry body and bold American and experimental hops for intense citrus flavor. The perfect spring seasonal, we invite you to enjoy this year’s Beer Camp encore.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-ISTT06-+1.The-2017-Sierra-Nevad-Beer-Camp-Across-the-World-12-pack-box.-image-courtesy-of-Sierra-Nevada-Brewing.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2012, 'v4KRep', '20th Anniversary Imperial Hash IPA on Brett', 9, 'Extremely hop forward with a residual sweetness; golden in color with a haze.The Brettanomyces used is a SweetWater house blend.  As fermentation finishes, the Brett will start to produce its associated acids and phenols, lending a slightly tart finish. The aroma is fruity, herbal, tropical and citrusy, and the Brett gives a nice touch of funk and earthy phenolics.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-v4KRep-+1.17903410_10155053820557752_4038537443084364483_n.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2013, 'e9sjBk', '21st Anniversary', 7.9, 'For our next few anniversary releases, we’re celebrating the beer mecca of Flanders, Belgium with a little east vs. west showdown. First off is an Oud Bruin (tr. Old Brown), which represents the style from the region of East Flanders. As the name indicates, this is an old style brown ale that uses a blend of microflora: bacteria such as acetobacter, lactobacillus and pediococcus; yeasts such as cultured saccharomyces yeast and brettanomyces wild yeasts to give the beer a specific sourness and funky aroma. We then aged it in American Oak foeders on top of cherries to give it a nice fruity punch that we know you’ll love.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-e9sjBk-+1.21st_overview_2.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2014, 'YZXVKq', '25th Anniversary', 9.8, 'Twenty Five is a special-release beer celebrating 25 years of craftsmanship from Breckenridge Brewery. Imperial Vanilla Porter Aged In Rum Barrels.', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-YZXVKq-+1.IMG_20190513_135527_aoj7d3.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2015, 'f5CWb6', '30th Anniversary - Charlie, Fred & Ken\'s Bock', 8.3, 'Charlie Papazian and Fred Eckhart are the men who launched a thousand breweries. Their writing on the art of homebrewing and steadfast promotion of beer culture helped propel the craft brewing movement. Charlie and Fred agreed to work with us on this special ale in honor of our 30th anniversary. This Imperial Helles Bock is a testament to the ever-evolving brewer’s art. Bold yet balanced with distinct toasted malt character, moderate sweetness and clean and floral hops.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-f5CWb6-+1.Sierra%2BNevada%2B30th%2BHelles%2BBock.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2016, '8M5lCq', '30th Anniversary - Jack & Ken\'s Ale', 10.2, 'Jack McAuliffe was the first American \"micro\" brewer. His tiny New Albion Brewery in Sonoma, California inspired countless dreamers to start small-scale breweries of their own. Jack agreed to guest brew this very special ale with us in honor of our 30th anniversary. This Black Barleywine Ale is a nod to the legendary ales New Albion served at their legendary summer solstice parties. Rich with bittersweet and roasted malt flavors, balanced with whole-cone American hops, this robust ale should age gracefully for years.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-8M5lCq-+1.IMG_2771.JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2017, 'NoNhan', '420 Extra Pale Ale', 5.4, 'SweetWater 420 Extra Pale Ale, our most popular brew, is a tasty West Coast-style pale ale with a stimulating hop character and a crisp finish. 1st brewed on April 20th 1997.\r\n\r\nGrains – Munich, 40L, 2-Row\r\nHops – Centennial, Cascade\r\n\r\nAwards – 2002 Silver Medal- Great American Beer Festival, 1997 – 2005 Creative Loafing Readers Choice – Best local beer, 1998 World Beer Cup silver medal, Top 10 Local beers – Atlanta Journal Constitution', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-NoNhan-+1.35128ee27de78fb4b706eda5852f01ee0ef141b4_sweetwater-420-pale.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2018, 'jIKwgZ', '420 Strain G13 IPA', 6, 'G13 IPA is a strange new strain, indeed. We took the dank hop profile you’d expect from a hazy IPA, and married it with terpenes and natural hemp flavors. The result is a big yet balanced IPA that mimics the aroma and taste of a heady, green G13. G13 IPA is a sticky super-hybrid that’s ready to rip.\r\n\r\nPungent and dank aromatics on this terpene infused IPA fill the room once the beer is opened. We went with an aggressive dry hop schedule which interlaces nicely with the unique flavors to bring forward citrus and earthy notes followed by a resinous finish. This one’s fire!\r\n\r\nColombus and Simcoe in the boil and dry hop!', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-jIKwgZ-+1.s3-420_strain_6_pack_3_1--default--1280.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2020, 'tw2Iw0', '471 IPA. Aggressive Hoppiness', 9.2, 'Hoppy? Brother, 471 IPA redefines hoppy. 471 is a small batch, limited edition ale that was created by our Brewmaster to separate the weak from the strong. 471 is a double IPA, that combines Pale, Munich, Caramel-30, Carapils and Torrified Wheat malts, with Chinook, Centennial, Simcoe and Fuggles hops. It has a big sweet mouthfeel, followed by more hoppiness than you\'ve ever had at one time. Enjoy.', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-tw2Iw0-+1.378601_0_1_1.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2021, 'j9cp5e', '471 Small Batch IPA', 9.2, 'Hoppy? Brother, 471 IPA redefines hoppy. 471 is a small batch, limited edition ale that was created by our Brewmaster to separate the weak from the strong. 471 is a double IPA, that combines Pale, Munich, Caramel-30, Carapils and Torrified Wheat malts, with Chinook, Centennial, Simcoe and Fuggles hops. It has a big sweet mouthfeel, followed by more hoppiness than you\'ve ever had at one time. Enjoy.', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-j9cp5e-+1.5f49c7bc810a0a62db525460475de712caafd488_breckenridge-471-dipa_4x6.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2022, '5MX880', '5 C\'s IPA', 6.5, 'Our interpretation of a West Coast IPA is golden, medium-bodied ale that is very hop forward.  The use of Cascade, Chinook, Columbus, Centennial and Crystal hops makes this beer a hophead\'s dream.', 'Portsmouth Brewery', 'New Hampshire', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-5MX880-+1.Five-on-Five-IPA-CBB34-header.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2023, 'uA3MVL', '7 Birds', 5, 'Strawberry, Raspberry pilsner. Very good. Crisp and clean. Beautiful disaster session style I could drink this all day while being outside.', 'Jackalope Brewing Company', 'Tennessee', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-uA3MVL-+1.lock-stock-dubbel-barrels-two-birds.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2024, 'Fhw2NF', '7 Cities Pilsner', 5, 'Seven Cities Pilsner, an unfiltered German Pilsner is the first lager style beer to be released by Jackalope Brewing Company.\r\n It is brewed entirely with noble German Tettnang hops and pours a beautiful light golden color,\r\n thus we named it after the myth of the Seven Cities of Gold.\r\n It is a light bodied, refreshing brew with hints of Pilsen malt sweetness,\r\n and a smooth yet hoppy finish.', 'Jackalope Brewing Company', 'Tennessee', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Fhw2NF-+1.-1x-1.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2025, 'MqTIG4', '72 Imperial', 7.2, 'Just sit back and enjoy the ride.\r\n\r\nBrewed with chocolate from Colorado\'s very own Rocky Mountain Chocolate Factory, Inc., this Imperial Chocolate Cream Stout is full of rich, toasted chocolate notes with hints of dark fruit. 72 Imperial will take you where you need to go. Just sit back and enjoy the ride.', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-MqTIG4-+1.72-Imperial-4-Pack-1024x776.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2026, 'wDgaK8', 'A Beer Named Sue', 5.7, 'Golden ale infused with local organic Artemesia Annua grown by Hallow Herb Farm in Burlington’s Intervale. The aroma and flavor of “Sweet Woodruff” meets fruity esters and soft malt character while finishing dry.', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-wDgaK8-+1.sue-pour.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2027, 'svXHfu', 'A Little Sumpin\' Sumpin\'', 7.5, 'Sneaky Smooth with a Touch of What we Call Wheatly-esque-ish-ness. Crispy Wheat and Pale Malt flavors with a Zippy Hop Finish. A Return of the Brand-Spankin’ New Beer From The Summer of 2009.', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-svXHfu-+1.Lagunitas-A-Little-Sumpin%E2%80%99-Sumpin%E2%80%99-Ale.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2028, '6AcqY6', 'Agave Wheat', 5.9, 'This true American-style unfiltered wheat has something a little special – the nectar of the great Salmiana Agave. Agave complements the refreshingly light quality of our wheat and adds a subtle note of flavor that expands this beer’s uplifting taste profile. It is familiar, yet creative.\r\n\r\nYeast: American Wheat\r\nMalts: Pale, White Wheat, Torrified Wheat, Carapils, Caramel, Munich\r\nHops: Fuggle, Cascade, Willamette', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-6AcqY6-+1.AW_3.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2029, 'yn4ODI', 'Ale Communication', 7.8, 'American Double IPA', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-yn4ODI-+1.026.JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2030, 'aG4Ie2', 'Alpha Dog Imperial IPA', 8.5, 'A True Hop Bomb Brewed plenty of Columbus and Mt Hood Hops for a Piney hop character. Premium Pale, Honey and Munich Malt make this beer a little less malty but packing plenty of hop punch.', 'Laughing Dog Brewing', 'Idaho', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-aG4Ie2-+1.Laughing+Dog+Alpha+Dog+Imperial+IPA.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2031, 'hYaduh', 'Alt Route - Beer Camp Across America', 6.6, 'Brewers are notorious for refusing to take the easy path. Instead, we lead with our hearts and pursue our passions no matter how difficult the road ahead. Alt Route is a tribute to this stubborn spirit that drove us to dodge the status quo and found breweries. Together we chased the siren song of beer with this revamped take on an antique beer style.\r\n\r\nLike us, Victory is one of the few brewers with an allegiance to whole-cone hops. They do extensive work with hop flavor, especially focusing on clever and delicious single-hop beers highlighting the same hop grown in different regions. They too share our roots in home brewing and never lost their passion for working with new beers and styles solely for the joy of making something new.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-hYaduh-+1.2014-08-04-23.21.24-2.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2032, 'Zd8Cxd', 'American Summer Hoppy Wit', 6, 'A spiced Belgian wit that is hopped with Citra, Amarillo, and Simcoe multiple times in the fermenter. Spicy and citrusy, with fruit flavors from the yeast and hops alike, with a tart twist at the finish.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Zd8Cxd-+1.Vesterbro_Belgian_Wit_New_1024x1024.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2033, 'b6nCMj', 'Anniversary Ale', 3.8, '7th Anniversary of American Flatbread/Zero Gravity being open. Session ale.', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-b6nCMj-+1.30th-Anniversary-BA-Sm.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2034, 'fBZZUJ', 'Anniversary Ale', 5.9, 'The 2007 Anniversary Ale features prominent usage of Cascade hops– the signature hop used in Sierra Nevada’s most popular product, Pale Ale. It is an American Style IPA with a big, fragrant pine and citrus hop aroma balanced by the sweetness of two-row pale and caramel malt. It finishes with an additional Cascade dry-hopping creating a big hop aroma Sierra Nevada fans will look forward to.  2007-2009, discontinued 2010.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-fBZZUJ-+1.30th-Anniversary-BA-Sm.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2035, 'ItEVNY', 'Anniversary Ale 2009', 5.9, 'From the Sierra Nevada Brewing Co. website:\r\nEach fall we celebrate our anniversary as one of AmericaÃ¢â?¬â?¢s craft brewing pioneers with a special beer.  This year, in celebration of our 27th year, we have made this beer available to the public for the first time, and aptly named it Anniversary Ale.    \r\n\r\nAnniversary Ale is an American-style IPA featuring Cascade hops, the signature hop used in our Pale Ale. The beer has a pronounced pine and citrus hop aroma balanced by the sweetness of two-row pale and caramel malts. The result is an unusually well-balanced IPA that proves an IPA can be both assertive and elegant. Anniversary Ale is a medium-bodied, well-hopped ale that finishes with a slight malt sweetness.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-ItEVNY-+1.alesmith-decadence-anniversary-ale-poured.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2036, 'IyyejS', 'Anubis Imperial Coffee Porter', 8, 'A complex Imperial Coffee Porter made with Evans Brothers cold-pressed coffee. Subtle chocolate, and coffee notes are balanced by black malt bitterness and malt sweetness.', 'Laughing Dog Brewing', 'Idaho', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-IyyejS-+1.imperial-porters.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2037, 'BJFSW8', 'Audition - Double IPA', 8.5, 'This beer is a true West Coast-style Double IPA made with huge amounts of hops - both in the kettle for flavor and later in the torpedo to impart a massive hop aroma. The light malt body and dry finish hide the power in this immensely drinkable hop-bomb.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-BJFSW8-+1.CzfVtJ-VIAAiZ8u.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2038, 'L0eAAB', 'Aunt Sally', 5.7, 'A Unique Dry-Hopped Sweet Tart Sour Mash Ale', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-L0eAAB-+1.IMG_8518.JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2040, 'kLnpDN', 'Bad Luck Blonde', 6.5, 'Ale Brewed with Coriander', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-kLnpDN-+1.NEW_Beer_1_Bottle_160718_fdb84fe3-ec0c-4d82-89c7-72a75be6bd63_1024x1024.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2041, 'J2UGn1', 'Baltic Anomaly', 8.5, 'Much like the alien mystery found at the bottom of the Baltic Sea, this Baltic Porter boasts an anomaly of its own. Honey lends an extraterrestrial dimension to this earthly porter, balancing out the sweetness with a slightly dry finish.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-J2UGn1-+1.tbd-new-holland-web-2.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2042, 'YXPOTZ', 'Bamberg Helles', 5.2, 'Golden German Lager with a touch of beech wood smoked malt. Brewed to pay homage to one of our favorite beers in Bamberg.', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-YXPOTZ-+1.Helles-Schlenkerla-Lager-from-Heller-Brauerei-beer-1.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2043, 'wRkDGh', 'Barrel Aged 471 IPA. Aggressive Hoppiness', 9.2, 'Hoppy? Brother, 471 IPA redefines hoppy. 471 is a small batch, limited edition ale that was created by our Brewmaster to separate the weak from the strong. 471 is a double IPA, that combines Pale, Munich, Caramel-30, Carapils and Torrified Wheat malts, with Chinook, Centennial, Simcoe and Fuggles hops. It has a big sweet mouthfeel, followed by more hoppiness than you\'ve ever had at one time. Enjoy.', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-wRkDGh-+1.5f49c7bc810a0a62db525460475de712caafd488_breckenridge-471-dipa_4x6.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2044, '8SiLJi', 'Barrel Aged Imperial Cherry Stout', 9.5, 'Aged in 50% Whiskey & 50% port wine barrels', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-8SiLJi-+1.breck-brew-imperial-cherry-stout.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2045, 'DvxCJ2', 'Barrel Aged Twenty Five', 9.8, 'Imperial Vanilla Porter Aged In Rum Barrels.', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-DvxCJ2-+1.desktop2x_1454461404_Bottle_tweak.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2046, 'xjSOtt', 'Barrel-Aged Porter', 7.4, 'A porter aged in bourbon barrels with vanilla beans & Cocoa nibs added', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-xjSOtt-+1.clf-bourbon-porter_580x@2x.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2048, '9YCuGj', 'Bearsharktopus', 6, 'Hoppy brett ale with fruit', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-9YCuGj-+1.WhNV0.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2050, 'pTHBWA', 'Beer Camp Hoppy Lager', 7, 'Beer Camp is the ultimate brewing experience. We bring beer fans into our brewery nearly every week to create their own beer with us—the more daring the better—and each spring we’ll highlight one of the small-batch standouts. Last year, Beer Camp worked overtime. Along with our fan brews, we made 12 additional beers with 12 exceptional breweries. Choosing one for an encore wasn’t easy. Ever drawn to hops, we decided to reimagine our hoppy lager collaboration with Ballast Point.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-pTHBWA-+1.07ab535fae12d01f5a334f6d0339d718.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2051, 'pGqazY', 'Beer Camp Tropical IPA', 6.7, 'Fruit-forward hops take this IPA to the tropics.\r\n\r\nBeer Camp is the ultimate brewing experience. We invite beer fans into our brewery nearly every week to design their own beer and then we bring it to life. Each spring, we’ll feature one of our favorite collaborations from the previous year. This year’s selection features intensely aromatic hop varietals rich with the flavors of the tropics. We use Citra, Mosaic and El Dorado hops to create bright fruit-forward flavors of mango, papaya and bitter orange.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-pGqazY-+1.IMG_0853.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2052, 'ZK2Swv', 'Beer Camp: Atlantic-Style Vintage Ale', 8.5, 'We\'re calling our Beer Camp collaboration an \"Atlantic Vintage Ale\" which combines elements from Fuller\' robust Vintage Ales with some American-style hopping techniques. We used plums in the brew to complement Fuller\'s naturally fruity yeast strain and we\'re bottle conditioning the beer for added longevity. This bee should age well in the bottle for years to come. Drink it now or stash some away to revisit in the future.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-ZK2Swv-+1.beercamp-atlanticStyleVintageAle.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2053, 'QHCtPE', 'Beer Camp: Dry Hopped Belgian Golden', 8, 'We\'re combining elements of Duvel\'s classic golden ale with Sierra Nevada\'s hop-forward fanaticism to create a new beer that highlights both. The complex fruity nature of Duvel\'s signature yeast is the first thing that greets you, followed shortly but a blast of bright, citrusy hops. The beer also has a touch of lemon peel for a po that greets the palate right at the finish of this deceptively drinkable and complex beer.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-QHCtPE-+1.beercamp-hoppyBelgianGolden.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2054, 'nxU5Fn', 'Beer Camp: Dry-Hopped Barleywine-Style Ale', 9.4, 'We\'re brewing a Dry-Hopped Barleywine Style Ale. Avery\'s founder, Adam Avery, was eager to brew this style and us this story: Sierra Nevada Bigfoot Barleywine inspired him to try his hand at the style, leading to the creation of Hog Heaven, an Avery brewing classic. The idea behind this beer for Beer Camp Across the World is actually not to \"collaborate\" at all, but, rather, to brew the exact recipe for Sierra Nevada\'s Bigfoot and the exact recipe of for Avery\'s Hog Heaven and blend the two distinct finished beers together, and then bottle condition a new version of these two classic beers. The resulting brew is lovingly dubbed \"Big Hog\" or \"HogFoot\" depending on the brewer\'s preference. It\'s big, intense, and hoppy. Great fresh or the perfect candidate for aging down the line.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-nxU5Fn-+1.beercamp-dryHoppedBarelyWine.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2055, '2avhYf', 'Beer Camp: Dry-Hopped Berliner-Style Weisse', 4.2, 'We wanted to make a beer that was a bit outside of both breweries\' normal wheelhouses, so together we chose to create a twist on the classic, tart, Berliner Weisse. We\'re playing off the slightly sour twang of the base beer by adding heaps of dry-hopped flavor to complement the tartness with citrusy and fruit-forward hop notes. The primary yeast strain is Sierra Nevada\'s famous Kellerweis wheat beer yeast, which imparts notes of banana and clove, blending seamlessly with the hops to create a dry, white-wine-like flavor that is as crisp and refreshing as anything we\'ve tried.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-2avhYf-+1.maxresdefault.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2056, 'eueVi6', 'Beer Camp: Dunkle Weisse', 5.7, 'We are brewing a classic Bavarian-Style Dunkle Weisse (Dark Wheat) beer. Ayinger\'s wheat beers are among the best produced anywhere in the world. We decided to bring together our two approaches to the style and create an all-new, rich, and malty version of the style. It\'s brewed in our open fermenter to allow the authentic Bavarian yeast strain to shine, with complex aromas of banana bread, caramel malt and cloves.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-eueVi6-+1.maxresdefault.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2057, 'z8iAm9', 'Beer Camp: East Meets West IPA', 7, 'An IPA, of course. We\'re blending our two approaches to the IPA in this East Meets West IPA. Sierra Nevada\'s malt body and profile was blended with the heavy-handed, very late hopping schedule employed by Tree House to create a new, hybrid IPA. Lightly bitter and heavy with citrus-like hop flavor.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-z8iAm9-+1.maxresdefault.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2058, 'SPbPNt', 'Beer Camp: Thai-Style Iced Tea', 7.2, 'Mikkeller has opened several world-class craft beer bars all over the world, most recently in Asia. We wanted to apply this globetrotting take to our collaboration brew. We found inspiration in a classic Thai iced tea: the spiced tea and condensed milk classic ubiquitous in Thai restaurants. The result is a spiced amber ale, brewed with black tea, sweet orange peel, tamarind and star anise with lactose added for a full and creamy mouthfeel.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-SPbPNt-+1.beercamp-mikkellerThaiStyleIcedTea-1024x850.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2059, '4jKDXK', 'Beer Camp: West Coast DIPA', 8.2, 'It was a given that when Sierra Nevada and Boneyard join forces to make a beer,  you\'re gonna get some type of an IPA. Together we\'re brewing an intense West Coast-Style Double IPA heavy with the classic hop character that defines both of our beers. It features Mosaic, Simcoe, Centennial and Citra hops in ridiculous amounts, sure to please the hopheads within us all.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-4jKDXK-+1.maxresdefault.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2060, 'h331gl', 'Beer Camp: White IPA with Yuzu', 7, 'Hitachino Nest\'s most popular beer is their White Ale, so it was a natural starting point for this collaboration. We opted to add hops (as we are known to do) and made a white IPA based on the flavor profile of the White Beer. Kiuchi suggested incorporating the use yuzu (a small Asian citrus fruit) into the brew, and we found the bright lime-like tartness perfectly accentuated the flavors of hops and the spicy notes of the classic witbier yeast.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-h331gl-+1.maxresdefault.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2061, 'ZJdowf', 'Beerhive', 8.47, 'Little John\'s local bees create a wildflower-honey which lends a sweet, earthy complexity to this traditional style beer.  A snap of ginger provides a a refreshing finish.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-ZJdowf-+1.Smartphone_aromas.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2062, '1cLpJP', 'Beerito', 4, 'Beerito is a light bodied, amber Mexican lager brewed with premium German and coloRADo sourced craft malts and featuring a crisp accent from noble hops. The mouth feel is incredibly smooth with flavors of walnut, toasted bread, plum, honey and cocoa - 4% ABV doesn\'t always come with this kind of character', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-1cLpJP-+1.oskar-blues-brewey-oskar-blues-beerito-amber-mexic.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2063, 'nAr0mR', 'Belgian Blond', 6.7, 'Golden Ale brewed with Belgian malts, candi sugar and Czech Saaz hops. This refreshing beer has a dry finish alongside fruity and spicy esters derived from the yeast.', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-nAr0mR-+1.wa-fles-gruut-belgian-blond.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2064, 'O3nY32', 'Bernie Weisse', 3.2, 'A slightly sour and forward-thinking ale.This beer gets it unique character from Lactobacillus. Served straight-up, or with your choice of raspberry, blueberry, or woodruff syrup. Tart, crisp, and refreshing. For an inside look at our Bernie Weisse canning run, check out Short-Fills NO. 9', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-O3nY32-+1.Bernie_Weisse.0.0.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2065, 'pSVIAZ', 'BFD - Beer For Drinking', 4.8, 'There are days when you want a beer—just a beer—that hits all the right spots. Well, this is it. No snifters required, no special occasions—just an unfussy, uncomplicated, hoppy blonde ale brewed to fit in no matter where it goes. This isn’t beer for collecting, this is beer for drinking.\r\n\r\nYEAST  Ale yeast\r\nBITTERING HOPS  Simcoe\r\nFINISHING HOPS  Polaris, Comet\r\nMALTS  Two-row Pale, Acidulated, Munich, Pilsner', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-pSVIAZ-+1.Sierra-Nevada-BFD.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2066, 'aztnLa', 'Bigfoot', 9.6, 'Our award-winning barleywine boasts a dense, fruity bouquet, an intense flavor palate and a deep reddish-brown color. Its big maltiness is superbly balanced by a wonderfully bittersweet hoppiness.\r\n\r\n\r\nMalts: Two Row Pale & English Carmel\r\nYeast: Ale Yeast\r\nBittering Hops: Chinook\r\nFinishing Hops: Cascade & Centennial\r\nDry Hops: Cascade, Centennial & Chinook', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-aztnLa-+1.sierra-nevada-bigfoot-beerinhawaii.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2067, 'pdLPeS', 'Bigfoot', 9.6, 'Our award-winning barleywine boasts a dense, fruity bouquet, an intense flavor palate and a deep reddish-brown color. Its big maltiness is superbly balanced by a wonderfully bittersweet hoppiness.\r\n\r\n\r\nMalts: Two Row Pale & English Carmel\r\nYeast: Ale Yeast\r\nBittering Hops: Chinook\r\nFinishing Hops: Cascade & Centennial\r\nDry Hops: Cascade, Centennial & Chinook', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-pdLPeS-+1.sierra-nevada-bigfoot-beerinhawaii.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2068, 'Rx4Dnt', 'Bigfoot', 9.6, 'Our award-winning barleywine boasts a dense, fruity bouquet, an intense flavor palate and a deep reddish-brown color. Its big maltiness is superbly balanced by a wonderfully bittersweet hoppiness.\r\n\r\n\r\nMalts: Two Row Pale & English Carmel\r\nYeast: Ale Yeast\r\nBittering Hops: Chinook\r\nFinishing Hops: Cascade & Centennial\r\nDry Hops: Cascade, Centennial & Chinook', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Rx4Dnt-+1.sierra-nevada-bigfoot-beerinhawaii.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2069, 'ysyw2P', 'Bigfoot', 9.6, 'Our cult-classic beast of a barleywine.\r\n\r\nBigfoot is a beast of a beer, brimming with bold flavors of bittersweet malt and heaps of aggressive whole-cone Pacific Northwest hops. First introduced in the winter of 1983, Bigfoot is a cult-classic beer brewed in the barleywine style, meaning a strong, robust, bruiser of a beer with the refined intensity of a wine. Bigfoot is prized by beer collectors for its supreme cellarability. Under the proper conditions, it can age like a fine wine, developing new flavors and character as it matures in the bottle. Each new release or “expedition” is vintage dated. Collect your own and see the flavors develop and progress.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-ysyw2P-+1.sierra-nevada-bigfoot-beerinhawaii.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2070, 'qUIYuC', 'Bigfoot', 9.6, 'Our award-winning barleywine boasts a dense, fruity bouquet, an intense flavor palate and a deep reddish-brown color. Its big maltiness is superbly balanced by a wonderfully bittersweet hoppiness.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-qUIYuC-+1.sierra-nevada-bigfoot-beerinhawaii.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2071, '0T4pOY', 'Bigfoot Barrel-Aged', 12.2, 'Our Bigfoot Barleywine is a craft beer legend. Each winter, this beast of a beer appears and wreaks havoc on unsuspecting palates with its intense bittersweet flavors. This year—in honor of the 30th Anniversary of this style-bending brew— we’re releasing a very special version of this cult classic: Aged in oak whiskey casks for nearly two years, this barrel-aged Bigfoot is incredibly complex. The assault of resinous hops has mellowed, and the influence of the wood has shifted focus toward the malt—with rich burnt-sugar flavors and notes of vanilla, toasted coconut, and raisins. Grab this elusive beast while you can, because it won’t be around for long.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-0T4pOY-+1.Sierra-Nevada-Barrel-Aged-Bigfoot.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2072, 'tLwMOd', 'Black Brew Bae', 6.4, 'Dark hop forward beer with supportive malts', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-tLwMOd-+1.ora%20440ml%20Can%20Mockup%20new%20logo.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2073, 'pkEofb', 'Black Cat Porter', 5.2, 'Avail normal or Cask w/ Chipotle peppers', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-pkEofb-+1.The%2BBlack%2BCat.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2074, 'kZadFf', 'Black IPA', 6.5, 'This IPA has the deep black color of a Stout, but the color leads your mind to expect a roasty acrid flavor to come through. Be prepared for this beer to trick your palate with the flavor and aromatics of a big hop bomb.  Greg Noonan would be pleased.  Cheers to Greg!', 'Portsmouth Brewery', 'New Hampshire', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-kZadFf-+1.black-ipa-2.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2075, 'fyj05b', 'Black IPA', 6.9, 'There is a debate raging in the beer world: dark vs. hoppy. Never ones to be bound by convention, we\'re combining them both in our newest Black IPA. Bright citrus and pine hop aroma and a hint of roasted malt flavor come together in this all-American beer mashup.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-fyj05b-+1.black-ipa-2.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2076, 'E6kkPh', 'Black Mad Hatter India Pale Ale', 5.56, 'A blackened version of Mad Hatter brewed with black malt for a dark, roasty sweetness to the base of the flavor profile. Finishes with a strong Centennial hop character from dry hopping.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-E6kkPh-+1.NewHollandBlackHatter.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2077, 'NgU9h0', 'Black Shack Porter', 5.3, 'Black, flavor abounding brew with chocolate mocha notes... so tasty!', 'Wachusett Brewing Company', 'Massachusetts', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-NgU9h0-+1.Dvh3XeiWoAAQAXe.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2078, 'Du7C2e', 'Black Tulip', 8.8, 'Mysterious, alluring and seductive, while tantalizingly elusive.  Ester-laden character reveals and enigmatic dance between Belgian ale yeast and Michigan beet sugar, conjuring hints of bananas before a dry finish.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Du7C2e-+1.Black+Tulip+(1).JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2079, '24mTU2', 'Blizzicane Bock', 7.7, 'In honor of an epic New England storm, a combination of a blizzard and a hurricane --a blizzicane-- that dumped several feet of snow and shut the coast for days, we bring you Blizzicane Bock, a dopplebock that\'s rich, thick and sweet with caramel and toffee flavor conceived in the hoary eye of that storm.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-24mTU2-+1.Troegs_Family.jpeg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2080, 'wzCyVT', 'Blue', 4.6, 'Sweetwater Blue is a unique light bodied ale enhanced with a hint of fresh blueberries. This euphoric experience begins with an appealing blueberry aroma and finishes as a surprisingly thirst-quenching ale.\r\n\r\nAward – 1998 World Beer festival Bronze Medal Winner – Fruit beer category', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-wzCyVT-+1.0006206730781.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2082, '8b9X23', 'Blue Goat', 7.5, 'Chestnut in color with a nutty malt profile from its signature Munich malt. A muted hop presence and smooth caramelized body culminate in a clean, dry finish. Excellent choice for hearty meals with dark flavors and sauces. Grilled meats, musty cheeses or pecan pie.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-8b9X23-+1.goat-beer-119.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2083, 'oYED15', 'Blue Ridge Red', 6.3, 'A hoppy red ale brewed with local honey.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-oYED15-+1.o87Dd5x.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2084, 'HQ79n0', 'Blue Sunday', 7, 'This unique anniversary libation, heritage-blended from our library of barrel-soured beers, exhibits deeply layered flavors of malt and oak, with a tart finish.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-HQ79n0-+1.2d24016dbbd9587540dd5eb136269a55eff76c18_new-holland-blue-sunday-sour-img_8339.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2085, '932XO8', 'Blueberry Ale', 4.5, 'Nice aroma of blueberry is balanced by a subtle flavor that gets fermented into this delicious brew.', 'Wachusett Brewing Company', 'Massachusetts', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-932XO8-+1.cq5dam.web.1280.1280.jpeg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2086, '5LwuwE', 'Bob White', 5, 'Our take on Belgian Wit, brewed with raw wheat and spiced with coriander and bitter and sweet orange peel.', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-5LwuwE-+1.zero-gravity-brewery-bob-white-belgian-witbier-beer-beverage-warehouse-vt.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2087, 'qpPzL7', 'Bobolink', 6.7, 'Brewed with organic pale malt, Jasmine rice, Carafoam malt and Northdown hops.', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-qpPzL7-+1.zero-gravity-bobolink-saison-vt-beer-beverage-warehouse-vermont.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2089, 'AEFy0R', 'Boomerang', 6.7, 'Boomerang is an American IPA that slings fruit-forward and floral flavors of Australian hops for an assertive, intercontinental escapes from winter’s grasp.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-AEFy0R-+1.img_20190306_1743071.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2090, 'HmjnXt', 'Born Again Yesterday', 7.5, 'We’ve discovered that the Lagunitas brewers are part time alchemists... they’ve figured out how to keep wet hops wet all freakin’ year long! The next beer in our 2016 #OneHitter Series is this Born Again Yesterday Pale Ale, which features a delicious concoction of wet hops, reborn and unfiltered into our Born Yesterday Pale Ale. Congrats... It’s a beer again!', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-HmjnXt-+1.maxresdefault.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2091, 'yORSh7', 'Bourbon Barrel Aged Imperial Stout', 11.2, 'This is the second edition from the brewery’s Cork & Cage series, a high-gravity, small-batch line-up that explores the edges of classic beer styles including barrel-aged beers, sours and wild ales. Bourbon Barrel Aged Imperial Stout is a supremely rich, full-bodied imperial stout laced with subtle notes of chocolate and bourbon, acquired while aging in bourbon barrels. A big beer at 11.2%, this is the highest ABV creation SweetWater will release this year.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-yORSh7-+1.braxton-2018-dark-charge.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2092, 't28a6A', 'Brandy Barrel-Aged Ten Fidy', 10.5, 'This is a collaboration between Appalachian Vintner and Oskar Blues Brevard. We brought them a fresh NC apple brandy barrel and they willingly filled with fresh Ten Fidy…Ten months ago! The resulting beer is absolutely tantalizing, world-class stuff.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-t28a6A-+1.BA_FIDY_webres-1200x1788.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2093, 'PRRZBx', 'Brass & Blues', 6.4, 'Collaboration with The Brass Tap.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-PRRZBx-+1.brass-diff-52_orig.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2094, 'hImGQV', 'Braupakt', 6, 'This naturally cloudy amber Hefeweissbier has a firm, creamy head and reveals fragrances of peach, apricot and citrus on the nose. The initial impression on the palate is of a bouquet of aromas, including subtle touches of banana plus refreshing grapefruit from the American Chinook hops. The fruity peach and apricot notes from the Amarillo hops are balanced by the gentle sweetness of the caramel malt. The beer has a delicate tartness that melds into a harmonious mouthfeel on the finish.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-hImGQV-+1.Weihenstephaner-Braupakt.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2095, 'KuiKeS', 'Breakfast At Chicos', 7.5, 'Breakfast at Chico’s in a Imperial Nitro Milk Stout with Almonds, brewed using lactose to boost the sweetness as well as ground almonds for a nutty flavor- glimpses of milk chocolate and coffee also emerge for a decidedly robust, creamy brew for when the sun’s rising or making way for evening antics. Other ingredients include two row pale, Munich, Honey, Brown and Oat malts with experimental and mosaic hops.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-KuiKeS-+1.4mogr0tb7ue21.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2096, 'IkgmFq', 'Breckenridge Christmas Ale', 7.4, 'The chill of a Colorado high-country winter calls for a beer with extra flavor and warming characteristics. Here it is. Breck Brew\'s Christmas Ale. At over 7% alcohol, with a sturdy texture and rich flavors of caramel and chocolate, our holiday seasonal is the fermented equivalent of a good fire.\r\n\r\nThe ultimate winter warmer.\r\n\r\nYeast:Top Fermenting Ale Yeast\r\nMalts:Two Row Pale, Caramel, Chocolate, Black\r\nHops:Chinook, Mt. Hood', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-IkgmFq-+1.Christmas%20Ale%20-%20Refresh%2012oz%20BTL.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2097, 'RcyKuX', 'Bretthead', 6.1, 'We brewed our popular Conehead IPA with a wild twist. Single-hopped with Citra and fermented with Brettanomyces wild yeast, this beer stands at the crossroads of hoppy and funky.', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-RcyKuX-+1.brevis-and-butthead-1024x1016.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2098, 'TpiDMC', 'Brown Shugga\'', 9.9, 'How Come you Taste So Good?? Boatloads of Pure Brown Sugar in Each Batch, That’s How! The Rich, Roasty and Mysteriously Drinkable Ale might best be described as... Irresponsible. It Leaves a Lot of Stories in it’s Wake.', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-TpiDMC-+1.Lagunitas+Brown+Shugga%27.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2099, 'd2nhC0', 'Brown\'s Point ESB', 5.6, 'This E.S.B. is definately the house favorite. Exclusively hopped with Fuggles, this full bodied amber ale finishes smooth and clean. 5.6% ABV', 'Harmon Brewing Company', 'Washington', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-d2nhC0-+1.bitch-creek2.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2100, 'GwYXdk', 'Brux', 8.3, 'What began as mutual admiration between Sierra Nevada’s Grossman Family and Russian River’s Cilurzos has grown and progressed into genuine friendship. Brux began as an idea and has grown into something altogether different: \r\n\r\nThe liquid manifestation of change over time. \r\n\r\nRefermented in the bottle with Brettanomyces bruxellensis, Brux will change and develop over time. Copper-colored, dry and complex, with slightly tart notes of green grass, pear, spice and lemon - this ale will progress in the bottle for many years.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-GwYXdk-+1.brux-for-web.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2101, 'P3fflp', 'Bubbly Wit', 7.1, 'A swanky interpretation of a double strength wheat beer, fermented solely by champagne yeast. Notes of tart citrus and white grape soothe the pallet in this sparkling ale.', 'Dock Street Brewery', 'Pennsylvania', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-P3fflp-+1.lowlander-wit-2-of-2-7.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2102, '8MMa77', 'Bud Dry', 5, 'Introduced in 1989 Bud Dry is the first dry-brewed beer produced by an American brewer. It is brewed with select hops, grains and barley malt, which results in a lighter body and less-sweet taste. As with all Anheuser-Busch beers, it is cold-filtered for a smooth draft taste, but then goes through a second cold-filtered finishing process to provide its unique taste.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-8MMa77-+1.maxresdefault.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2103, 'W2dlxg', 'Bud Extra', 6.6, 'Originally known as B-to-the-E', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-W2dlxg-+1.gettyimages-1005678174-e1549556607341.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2104, 'SaQFBA', 'Bud Ice Light', 4.1, 'Introduced in 1994.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-SaQFBA-+1.Article-Remember-Bud-Ice-Budweiser-Beer.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2105, 't9aucT', 'Bud Light Chelada', 4.2, 'Bud Light & Clamato Chelada, combines Bud Light with the refreshing taste of Clamato, spices and a hint of lime. To best enjoy Bud Light & Clamato Chelada, gently rotate the chilled can once before pouring. Then, serve cold, or pour over ice, into a traditional goblet-style glass and garnish with a slice of lime or celery stalk.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-t9aucT-+1.4ff3f3e6-237f-43fc-84e2-df14199d95dc_1.fd10b7c07394c25a0422168c57d4080f.jpeg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2106, 'MzoCPz', 'Bud Light Lime', 4.2, 'Bud Light Lime, introduced in 2008, is a premium light lager that combines the superior drinkability of Bud Light with 100 percent natural lime flavor.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-MzoCPz-+1.BUD-LIGHT-LIME-12PK-NR-12OZ-Beer.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2107, 'VwOYAS', 'Bud Light Lime Mang-O-Rita', 8, 'Bud Light Lime Mang-O-Rita combines two favorites: the delicious taste of a mango margarita and the refreshment of Bud Light Lime. Best-served over ice, Bud Light Lime Mang-O-Rita is perfect for any outdoor occasion.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-VwOYAS-+1.15164.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2108, 'hd8yE8', 'Bud Light Platinum', 6, 'Bud Light Platinum has reinvented the category of light beer. Within each cobalt blue bottle lies a bold formula that\'s triple filtered with a smooth finish to create its top shelf taste. It\'s the first of its kind, and the only beer worthy of the name Bud Light Platinum.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-hd8yE8-+1.fffa2c57-b0e0-448f-80d5-1d561f129578_1.f83d431acf607a147f80ec89a3b99aec.jpeg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2109, 'LXWiDB', 'Bud Light Radler - Grapefuit', 2.4, 'A perfect mix of light beer and real fruit juice, this favourite combines citrus flavours and grapefruit aroma with a refreshing taste.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-LXWiDB-+1.cq5dam.web.1280.1280.jpeg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2110, '1P45iR', 'Budweiser', 5, 'Known as “The King of Beers”, Budweiser was first introduced by Adolphus Busch in 1876 and is brewed with the same high quality standards today. Budweiser is a medium-bodied, flavorful, crisp American-style lager, craft brewed with a blend of premium hop varieties, and associated with the core American values of celebration and optimism.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-1P45iR-+1.51L4SsgPS5L._SL1000_.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2111, 'hlynwj', 'Budweiser American Ale', 5.1, 'Budweiser American Ale is brewed with barley from America\'s heartland and dry hopped with Cascade hops from the Pacific Northwest.\r\n\r\nAvailable Fall 2008.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-hlynwj-+1.beer-hops.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2112, 'eW9IJb', 'Budweiser Chelada', 5, 'Budweiser & Clamato Chelada, combines Budweiser with the refreshing taste of Clamato, spices and a hint of lime. To best enjoy Budweiser & Clamato Chelada, gently rotate the chilled can once before pouring. Then, serve cold, or pour over ice, into a traditional goblet-style glass and garnish with a slice of lime or celery stalk.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-eW9IJb-+1.cb045f74-b99c-43de-af66-c1582e7747ff_1.f47adbbf97488e46ac3d9e1df0a4443b.jpeg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2113, 'mobjLC', 'Budweiser Copper Lager', 6.2, 'This is a flavorful American Copper Lager brewed with two-row barley malt and aged on real Jim Beam bourbon barrel staves for a toasted oak aroma, a deliciously nutty taste with caramel rye and vanilla notes, and a smooth finish.\r\n\r\nBudweiser Brewmasters and Jim Beam\'s Master Distillers have created this brew in honor of the 85th anniversary of the Repeal of Prohibition on December 5, 1933.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-mobjLC-+1.Copper-Lager.jpeg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2114, 'bQk5Rn', 'Budweiser Freedom Reserve', 5.4, 'The Freedom Reserve is a specialty red lager brewed with toasted barley grains for a slightly sweet aroma with a touch of hops, a rich caramel malt taste, and a smooth finish with a hint of molasses. Inspired by George Washington\'s recipe.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-bQk5Rn-+1.bud-freedom-reserve.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2115, 'jjIwuS', 'Budweiser Prohibition Brew', 0.5, 'When you need something done right, you have to do it yourself. Budweiser Prohibition Brew is a non-alcoholic beer that actually tastes like beer. All the crisp, clean taste you’ve come to expect from Budweiser. Brewed to the same standards you’ve come to expect from Budweiser.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-jjIwuS-+1.3588d5e1c4a26eb0188a55cf8d1fc707.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2116, 'G2Vi1J', 'Budweiser Select', 4.3, 'Bud Select is a new beer offering a bold taste with a full and distinct flavor that finishes clean. Budweiser Select was developed using two-row and roasted specialty malts for a rich color. It offers excellent drinkability and a taste that does not linger.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-G2Vi1J-+1.0001820007985_1200.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2117, 'BbrPm8', 'Buffalo Trace Aged Scotch Ale', 11.1, 'Sierra Nevada’s traditionally styled Scotch Ale is deep red in color, possessing a strong malt flavor with a very light hop character derived from the English hops used. Though medium bodied, this sweet ale is rather potent at 7.3% ABV. To add even more character to this beer, we aged it in bourbon barrels for eight months.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-BbrPm8-+1.WoodenCask-Corruption-Cover.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2118, 'QhHBBX', 'Busch', 4.6, 'Busch offers a refreshingly smooth taste. Since being introduced regionally in 1955, the Busch beer brand family has grown to become one of the top-selling value beer brand families. Busch also holds a noted place in Anheuser-Busch history as the first new brand after the repeal of Prohibition.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-QhHBBX-+1.001820000063.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2119, 'fKinUP', 'Busch Ice', 5.9, 'Busch Ice has a rich, smooth taste with exceptional drinkability and a slightly sweet finish. Busch Ice undergoes Anheuser-Busch\'s exclusive ice-brewing process, which takes the beer to a temperature below freezing. This leads to the formation of ice crystals in the finishing process, which help create its rich, smooth taste.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-fKinUP-+1.1308H.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2120, '30zzKy', 'Busch Light', 4.1, 'Busch Light offers a light, balanced flavor, with fewer calories. It has a pleasant hop aroma and a smooth, slightly sweet finish.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-30zzKy-+1.Busch-Light-Beer-12-pk-12-fl.-oz.-Cans.jpeg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2121, 'vNwXnT', 'Busch Signature Copper Lager', 5.7, 'Busch Signature Copper Lager satisfies the needs of value consumers who are looking for a beer with slightly more flavor that still finishes smooth for those slightly more special occasions.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-vNwXnT-+1.Busch-Signature-Copper-Lager.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2122, 'zYJxUM', 'Cabin Fever', 6.5, 'Cabin Fever is a roasty brown ale and a hearty, comforting companion for long, mind-bending winters.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-zYJxUM-+1.JS-Cabin-Fever-345mL-Bottle-n-Glass-SPRITZ-1mb.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2123, '9OyQXs', 'California Black Beer', 4.9, 'A deceptively light bodied dark beer.  This is a refreshing beer with a macho color.  The emphasis is on the malts: light caramel notes with a finish that hints at chocolate and coffee. Ends dry in the mouth.', 'Last Name Brewing', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-9OyQXs-+1.b11cfe2d6ec7fe2cc83ff55092c5edca12df83bf_bear-republic-big-bear-black-stout-1360px.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2124, 'GTbXLB', 'Cambium', 5.8, 'Foeder aged golden sour ale.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-GTbXLB-+1.57131082_2087423678021678_6469904959071584256_o.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2125, 'xpBGZB', 'CANfusion - Beer Camp Across America', 7.2, 'Our friends at Oskar Blues pioneered great beer in a can and, as mutual members of the canned craft club, this partnership was a perfect fit. CANfusion is a coming together—a fusion, if you will—of flavors from across the spectrum of brewing: spicy rye, tangy wheat and a bright citrusy hop aroma.\r\n\r\nOskar Blues is the granddaddy of canned craft beer. Like us, they have a fun-loving passion for the outdoors and bikes. It was a natural fit for them to adopt cans as a portable, durable way to tote their favorite beer on the trail, and in the process they  paved the way for all other craft brewers to follow.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-xpBGZB-+1.beercamp2014-chico-torpedopilsner-set.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2126, 'qa1QZU', 'Cappuccino Stout', 8.9, 'Big, Dark and Scary Imperial-esque Stout Brewed With Plenty of Dark Malts and Roast Barley And Loads of Sebastopol’s Hardcore Coffee for Even Bigger Roasty Flavors and that Extra Krunk.', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-qa1QZU-+1.Cappuccino-Stout.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2127, 'KY5gtZ', 'Celebration Ale', 6.8, 'The long, cold nights of winter are a little brighter with Celebration® Ale. Wonderfully robust and rich, Celebration® Ale is dry-hopped for a lively, intense aroma. Brewed especially for the holidays, it is perfect for a festive gathering or for a quiet evening at home.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-KY5gtZ-+1.sierra-nevada-celebration-ale.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2128, 'tZkS7X', 'Censored Imperial Stout', 9.9, '35 IBU', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-tZkS7X-+1.Lagunitas-Brewings-Cappuccino-Stout-and-Dry-Hopped-Censored-Ale.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2129, 'GboTWT', 'Censored Rich Copper Ale', 6.75, 'The original name of the original ale was originally derived from an origin so heinous that we cannot reveal its aboriginal orogeny. Sorry.  Actually it\'s easy drinking malty copper ale that goes easy on the hops. Whatever.', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-GboTWT-+1.lagunitas-censored-rich-copper-ale-aka-the-kronik.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2130, 'lUt8yP', 'Charkoota Rye', 8.4, 'A malty backbone of rye and four other malts, including malted barley smoked over cherry wood. Its smoke-forward body is balanced with tones of deep molasses and caramel, with a crisp, clean lager finish.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-lUt8yP-+1.New%2BHolland%2BCharkoota%2BRye.JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2131, 'zhzeah', 'Cherry Jane', 5.5, 'This sweet tart sour ale is full of Turkish Delight cherries, giving it a puckered up punch of cherry charm, then it\'s fermented with some Brettanomyces for that extra funky funk. We love you, Cherry Jane. Do ya?', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-zhzeah-+1.maxresdefault.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2132, '3wh93y', 'Chewbocka', 6.2, 'Deep amber lager using all German ingredients. This beer is malt forward and exceptionally drinkable. No Wookiees were harmed in the brewing of this beverage.', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-3wh93y-+1.DwaRyg1VAAAAlXB.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2134, 'dnUKxu', 'Chocolate Chili Stout - High Altitude Series', 8.8, 'By their very nature, imperial stouts are bold beers. This version takes another step toward the dark side with the use of spicy and aromatic dried chilies and rich cocoa nibs for a complex and intense kick. It features notes of coffee, baker’s cocoa, and dark fruit and a slight twinge of heat.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-dnUKxu-+1.6NmmdHl.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2135, 'T1YdsG', 'Chocolate Pretzel Stout', 5.2, 'Stout brewed with chocolate and pretzels.', 'Jackalope Brewing Company', 'Tennessee', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-T1YdsG-+1.ps12oz.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2136, 'EBgR2m', 'Choice Make Good', 8.3, 'This Double IPA was brewed with Amarillo, Centennial, 007, Nelson Sauvin, Azacca, and Citra Hops. Additionally, we dry-hopped in the fermenter with a blend of Nelson Sauvin and Citra. Make good choices.', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-EBgR2m-+1.beer-subscription-boxes-hero.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2137, 'zpvlri', 'Christmas Chub', 8, 'Brewed with orange peel and Colorado spruce.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-zpvlri-+1.img_20150625_094511.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2138, 'mXym9s', 'Coffee Stout', 6.2, 'A cup of joe and a bold beer can thwart the winter cold, so we blended them for the ultimate warmer. Our Coffee Stout is a fusion of dark roasted malts and rich, cold-brewed coffee for layers of bittersweet, fruity, dark chocolate and caramel-like flavors.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-mXym9s-+1.CoffeeMockUp.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2139, 'h2d5zt', 'Conehead', 5.7, 'Our single hop wheat IPA, brewed with all Citra hops. Lighter in color and lower in a.b.v. than a typical American IPA, this beer has just the right amount of hop flavor and aroma. Completely satisfyingly awesome in its crispiness and well-rounded hopaliciousness. This beer might just be your Rushmore.', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-h2d5zt-+1.ZG_Conehead.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2140, 'ehb1eB', 'Country Pale Ale', 5.1, 'Our original brew crafted by Ned, Kevin and Quinny in the early 90\'s with super drinkability.', 'Wachusett Brewing Company', 'Massachusetts', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-ehb1eB-+1.img_2928.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2141, 'bHmQdD', 'Crank Tank', 5.8, 'We cranked the fermentation temps down to a chilly 11 degrees celsius and went with a longer lagering on this Helles prior to filtration. Bright and balanced with the clean and crisp finish of traditional Munich style lagers, Crank Tank is very quaffable after any long ride.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-bHmQdD-+1.sweetwater-crank-tank.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2142, 'xwLUUb', 'Cream Ale', 5, 'This is a traditional Cream Ale fermented with both ale and lager yeasts. Brilliant clarity with a malt aroma and a soft, malty sweetness.', 'Laughing Dog Brewing', 'Idaho', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-xwLUUb-+1.bk10380-beer.simply.beer-creamale.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2143, 'iT9pf4', 'Dale\'s Pale Ale', 6.5, 'Dale\'s Pale Ale is our flagship beer and America\'s first hand-canned craft beer. It\'s an assertive but deftly balanced beer (somewhere between an American pale ale and an India Pale Ale) brewed with hefty amounts of European malts and American hops.\r\n\r\nIt features a merengue-like head, a copper color, and a hoppy nose, thanks to a big post-boil addition of Centennial hops. To complement its hoppy first impression, Dale\'s also sports a rich middle of malts and hops, and a bracing finish. Dale\'s is 6.5% alcohol by volume, and features 65 International Bittering Units.\r\n\r\nWe think of it as the perfect, everyday beer for hopheads like us. Dale\'s Pale Ale\'s rich flavor has helped us make many new fans, and its numerous honors have helped us kick huge holes in the misconceptions regarding cans.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-iT9pf4-+1.DPA_webres.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2144, '2ADEYR', 'Dale\'s Pale Ale Nitro', 6.5, 'This voluminously hopped mutha delivers a hoppy nose and assertive-but-balanced flavors of pale malts and citrusy floral hops from start to finish. Oskar Blues launched its canning ops in 2002, brewing and hand-canning Dale’s Pale Ale in the Lyons, Colorado, brewpub. America’s first-craft-canned mountain pale is a hearty, critically acclaimed trailblazer that changed the way craft beer fiends perceive portable beer', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-2ADEYR-+1.DPA_webres.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2145, 'LR5oG8', 'Dank Tank BSP Quad', 11, 'Belgian, Strong, Pause . . . for a moment and let’s consider the Possibilities. Sure, you were thinking Pale but it’s not at all pale. Rather the contrary. The P could stand for Perfect: perfectly befitting a warm respite in front of a fire on a cold February night – but we don’t say chit like that. You’ll probably just drink this Belgian Quad like a session beer and hope for the best in the morning anyway, so screw it. Maybe the P stands for your favorite Pub, the place where you go to hang out, drink killer beer and enjoy life. Yup, that’s the one. The Quad part, well it’s a style for sure, but it could be in reference to a collaboration between a Pub and a Brewhouse that opened in the same year out of friendships and a love for great beer. Yeah, those four things are in here too.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-LR5oG8-+1.DZfJtQ1XUAEtmNr.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2146, '69tWZj', 'Dank Tank Ghoulash', 8.5, 'Alone and cold on a frigid fall night, the evil Dr. Dank’s stomach rumbled. It had been days since devouring the last of his trannies and platypuseses. Desperate, he wandered into his kitchen only to find a 3-eyed rat, yellow toenails, and an old bean burrito. Always resourceful, Dr. Dank remembered his great, great, bouffalata, granny goose’s Ghoulash recipe.  Try as he might, he couldn’t get it right, so he dumped everything he could find from the fridge and cupboard into one giant boiling brew, resulting in this stew of 2-row, black wheat, munich malt and a 14-hop variety asplifidation of Willamette, Galena, Mt. Hood, Nugget, Perle, Aroma, Bobek, Aurora, Styrian, Golding, Magnum, Columbus, Summit, Millennium, and Crystal.\r\n\r\nSloppy seconds never tasted so ghood!', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-69tWZj-+1.swb_dt_ghoulash_sellsheet_110922_02je_m.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2147, 'ov7fgF', 'Dank Tank Pulled Porter', 7.7, 'Welcome back to the Dank Tank Series! This brew features rich and smokey bacon notes, wrapped in a medium-full body and a relatively high ABV.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-ov7fgF-+1.swppbanner.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2148, '9nXV0D', 'Dank Tank The Price is Wrong', 9, 'Workin’ as a caddy at Bushwood, El Danko was stoked to ?nd out he would be shouldering Boob Barker’s bag. Figuring Boob was a swell guy who liked to have fun, El Danko slipped an exploding golf ball onto the ?rst tee. Boob was so enraged after the ball blew, he threw a haymaker at El Danko and broke his high heel. Fearing a big lawsuit and being hammered in the tabloids, Boob offered him a rigged spot on the Price is Wrong to keep him quiet. Sure enough, down in Studio City 42 days later, Rod Roddy bellowed out to El Danko “C’mon down!” He was ecstatic as they wheeled out some fancy leather chaps and some extra crisping hair mousse, which he just purchased last week. Bidding $420 on the lot, El Danko nailed it! With a kiss from Barker ’s Beauties as the bonus, he strutted on stage and with a wink he gave a slap on the ass to Boob Barker himself. On to the big prize, El Danko was confronted with the infamous Cliff Hanger climb! Just as the yodeler was about to cliff dive off the ledge, he came to a screeching halt. The Dankster had pulled it off, winning the prize behind Door #2: Pimpin’ high heels and some private time behind Curtain #3 with Ester-y, the Belgian Barker Beauty, who 9 months later delivered the biggest surprise of all! Blam!!! El Danko is a dad living in Belgium. Jobless, he got a gig at Ester-y’s family brewery to pay for his Price is Wrong love child, Bar nold Schwarzenkegger. The Boob Barker Belgian Behemoth Boogieboy. Benjoy!', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-9nXV0D-+1.sweetwater-price-is-wrong.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2149, '0HZF08', 'Dark Swan', 8.7, 'An experimentally hopped sour ale fermented with dark red wine grapes.\r\n\r\nObservers of yestercentury once doubted the existence of the Dark Swan, stating the fair-feathered fowl was the only color of its kind. Explorers eventually upended that theory, shocking the world and shining light on the Dark. This beer might just do the same. It’s a sour ale fermented with dark red wine grapes, giving it its uniquely deep and rich purple hue. Then it received the signature Lagunitas treatment with a healthy dose of experimental dry hops. This might just shock your taste buds!', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-0HZF08-+1.2b757cb1d8eeef0fa6b4b88f1d140eb4.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2150, '6f6SpY', 'Das Bij', 5.6, 'We use local honey and thyme\r\n to give the brew a dry, herbal quality that compliments the\r\n noble hops. With a light, champagne-like body, it’s the perfect way to close\r\n out the long dog days of summer.', 'Jackalope Brewing Company', 'Tennessee', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-6f6SpY-+1.collection-of-dutch-craft-beers-bij-brewery-brouwerij-t-ij-isolated-KT0JD6.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2151, '24UMt9', 'Davey Murray\'s Best Scotch Ale', 9.5, 'This Scotch Ale is sweet, but not cloying. It\'s strong, but not brash. It\'s smooth and smokey, like a good dram among friends. Cheers!\r\n\r\n\"O gude ale comes and gude ale goes; Gude ale gars me sell my hose,  Sell my hose, and pawn my shoon- Gude ale keeps my heart aboon!\" Cheers to the great Bard of Ayrshire for this ale’s epitaph: There is a beer, whose clarity’s clear, can teach the mash paddle to steer, and fuels the brewer\'s mad career. This ale within is fine to brew and quick to know, and keenly felt by the friendly glow, and softer flame, of the heartful jolly soul that wears this name. Beer-lover, attend! Whether thy soul soars in fancy’s flight, or on this earthly whole in low pursuit, know water, barley, hops, and yeast are Davey Murray’s root.', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-24UMt9-+1.Lagunitas%2BDavey%2BMurray%2527s%2BBest%2BScotch%2BAle.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2152, 'qgR2pv', 'DayTime Ale', 4.65, 'A Fractional IPA. \r\nSometimes you want a beer, then you realize how much crap you need to do before you call it a day. This is it. Nicely dosed with Big, Round Hop Flavors and a Toasty Malt Foundation to satisfy your every need. But it still lets you stay in the game to do what needs to be done. Yup.', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-qgR2pv-+1.a5b91a9ac65fad856b220883a8282c31e2dcee73_lagu-daytime.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2153, 'MDLWPq', 'De Achste Hond Peach Sour', 7, 'Laughing Dogs Take on a sour Fruit Beer.  Lightly Tart with a huge Peach nose, a hint of oak and a champagne like finish', 'Laughing Dog Brewing', 'Idaho', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-MDLWPq-+1.VellaDryJack-1.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2154, 'HXVdFT', 'Death By Coconut', 6.5, 'Death By Coconut is an Irish porter aged on dessicated coconut and dark chocolate from Robin Chocolates in Longmont.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-HXVdFT-+1.DBC_webres.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2155, '4nRKTH', 'DevESTATEtion', 6.7, 'When the going gets bad, we make great beer.\r\n\r\nIt’s a shame when good barley goes bad. This spring, the combined effect of double digit sustained winds and concentrated rainfall created major stress on the normal course of our barley maturation — our crop went down for the count. Instead of crying in our beer—or lack thereof—we decided to do one better and make something new. Featuring organic malts and our estate-grown wet hops, this black IPA is the evil twin of our legendary Estate Ale. Black in color with a mild roasty flavor and moderate body, this beer has a bold citrusy and earthy hop flavor and aroma from the use of our own wet hops. We’d never let one bad harvest get in the way of a great beer, so join us in a toast to the memory of our devastating season.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-4nRKTH-+1.2014-06-25-sierra-nevada-devestatetion-1.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2156, '7dkC8e', 'Deviant Dale’s', 8, 'Deviant Dale’s IPA was born at the crossroads, in a juke joint, as if Dale’s Pale Ale sold its soul to balance Deviant’s foreboding aromas of citrus, grapefruit rind and piney resins with a copper ball-of-fire color and inscrutable finish. The 2011 GABF Silver Medal Winner (American IPA Category) is the Devil incarnate with untold amounts of malt and hedonistic Columbus dry-hopping. Oskar Blues’ southern spirit caught a northbound blues bus to ColoRADo to deliver the boundary bustin’ brewery’s first 16 oz. tallboy can.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-7dkC8e-+1.DPA_webres.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2157, 'RDEj6L', 'Devil Dog Imperial IPA', 10.8, 'An all out assault on the senses. Devil Dog is an Imperial IPA with a floral / citrus hop aroma and flavor. This beer ages well and will take on some barley wine characteristics with time.', 'Laughing Dog Brewing', 'Idaho', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-RDEj6L-+1.dscn5782.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2158, 'cOSoch', 'Dire Wolf', 6.2, 'The Dire Wolf encorporates five additions of both Simcoe and Amarillo hops. Each addition was carefully planned to createoptimal bitterness and a strong, fresh aroma of grapefruit and pine. We paired these hops with an extremely pleasent malt flavor makes this a giant amongst IPAs.', 'Jackalope Brewing Company', 'Tennessee', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-cOSoch-+1.b81fe58cae75bf28ec3d032eac30cafa.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2159, 'NE2Dpl', 'Dogs of Helles', 4, 'A crisp and refreshing light lager. \r\nPredominantly pale malt leaves little residual sweetness.\r\nIt uses corn as a subtle flavor enhancer, and gives the beer a smooth character.', 'Laughing Dog Brewing', 'Idaho', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-NE2Dpl-+1.helles-large.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2160, 'aabOus', 'DogZilla Black IPA', 6.9, 'Laughing Dog Dogzilla Black IPA is a true Northwest IPA with a big hop presence and a dark malt twist in the finish. 68.4IBU.  The black IPA style is something new but this beer from Laughing Dog a standout that has to be tasted to be appreciated.', 'Laughing Dog Brewing', 'Idaho', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-aabOus-+1.045+Dogzilla+Black+IPA.JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2162, 'LVSSPk', 'Double Latte - Beer Camp Across America', 7.6, 'Inspired by the perennial café favorite, Double Latte combines two of the greatest things in life: good coffee and great beer. Oregon’s Ninkasi Brewing knows their way around a good cup of joe. Featuring cold-press coffee from the legendary Stumptown Coffee Roasters and a dose of milk sugar, this coffee milk stout is a rich and roasty treat.\r\n\r\nThis young-gun brewery has a locomotive charge. A rich conversation at a local bottle shop in 2005 has morphed into a Pacific Northwest staple. Named after the Sumerian goddess of fermentation, Ninkasi’s first batch of beer was Total Domination IPA and it remains a must for those with a lupulin itch.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-LVSSPk-+1.Sierra+Nevada+Beer+Camp+Across+America+Double+Latte+2.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2163, 'WHQisc', 'Dragon\'s Milk', 11, 'A barrel-aged, strong-ale with a soft and rich caramel-malt character intermingled with deep vanilla tones dancing in an oak bath. Unmistakably distinctive and hauntingly remarkable, Dragon\'s Milk\'s warming complexity pairs well with smoked meats and cheeses, red meat, or a nice cigar.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-WHQisc-+1.dragons-milk-og-updated.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2164, 'ZDbYzs', 'Dragon\'s Milk Reserve Coconut Rum', 11, 'Coconut complements the roasted chocolate flavor of Dragon\'s Milk, coaxing flavors that are reminiscent of lazy summer days. Rum barrels add a tropical character.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-ZDbYzs-+1.a092b2c32a8f2d447208b08b1a4fc5fb.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2165, 'uhfEWi', 'Dragon\'s Milk Reserve Mexican Spice Cake', 11, 'Aged in bourbon barrels for three months, with toasted chiles, cocoa nibs, vanilla, and cinnamon added during aging.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-uhfEWi-+1.oe7otfbr36vy.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2166, 'RXEBYd', 'Dragon\'s Milk Reserve Vanilla Chai', 11, 'Combines robust malt character with the luxurious nuance of sweet Chai. Aged in white-oak bourbon barrels, Vanilla Chai Dragon’s Milk is a concert of luscious flavors.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-RXEBYd-+1.dragons_milk_vanilla.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2167, 'ZJJ8yY', 'Dragon\'s Milk Reserve: Cherry Chocolate', 11, 'Dragon\'s Milk Reserve Cherry Chocolate brings two classic flavors together, chocolate notes paired perfectly with the tartness of cherry will delight your senses.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-ZJJ8yY-+1.New-Holland-Dragons-Milk-Reserve-Cherry-Chocolate-1.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2168, 'DwfEan', 'Dragon\'s Milk Reserve: Raspberry Lemon', 11, 'This reserve blend is aged in bourbon barrels for three months, with Michigan raspberries and lemon zest added during aging.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-DwfEan-+1.new-holland-craft-beer-dragons-milk-raspberry-lemon-variant.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2169, 'Y6iD9x', 'Dragon’s Milk Reserve with Raspberries', 11, 'This beer is from our collection of special variations that live in our Dragon’s Milk cellar. Local raspberries were added to the barrels in the final stages of conditioning. Raspberries lend depth, brightness and unique fruit character that harmonizes beautifully with Dragon’s Milk dark, roasty tones of malt, bourbon and oak.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Y6iD9x-+1.new-holland-dragons-milk-reserve-raspberry-hibiscus-12oz-bottle_1600x.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2170, 'hqQhp6', 'Dry Irish Stout', 4.8, 'Jet black and true to style 100% Maris otter base malt and an English ale yeast bring complexity to an otherwise simple yet traditional grain bill toasty yet dry and drinkable.', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-hqQhp6-+1.dry-irish-stout-3.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2171, 'utrZWH', 'Dubbel', 7.4, 'Made with Belgian malt, wheat, dark candi sugar and East Kent Goldings hops. Dark amber with fruity esters and great malt complexity.', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-utrZWH-+1.trappist_westmalle_dubbel__1164.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2172, 'RsTK7E', 'Dude of York', 4.5, 'A light English-Style ale that showcases Maris Otter malt, Bramling Cross hops, and English ale yeast.  Only the water is not imported.', 'Last Name Brewing', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-RsTK7E-+1.snapseed-19-1.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2173, 'jcxBhr', 'el Mole Ocho', 8.4, 'Our exploration into the flavors of mole, the legendary sauce of central Mexico. Malty aroma and rich, cocoa-laden body laced with an invigorating tinge of dries chilies and coffee.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-jcxBhr-+1.dsc05841.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2174, 'YBxI4X', 'El Mole Ocho', 10, 'Our exploration into the flavors of mole, the legendary sauce of central Mexico. Malty aroma and rich, cocoa-laden body laced with an invigorating tinge of dries chilies and coffee.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-YBxI4X-+1.dsc05841.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2175, 'jBjeGJ', 'Electric Ray - Beer Camp Across America', 8.5, 'As ever, San Diego’s Ballast Point looked to the sea for the inspiration behind Electric Ray. A play on the fish’s scientific name—Torpedo californica—this beer pays homage to our mutual home state, as well as to our Hop Torpedo, the source of much of the big flavor in this high voltage, hop-forward Imperial Pale Lager.\r\n\r\nBallast Point brought their homebrewing dreams to the big leagues and started brewing professionally, but they never forgot their roots. They still run a successful homebrewing supply shop in San Diego.  A love for hops and the ocean inspire incredible brewed and distilled offerings, and their one-of-a-kind labels boast some beautiful, and sometimes gnarly-lookin’, fish.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-jBjeGJ-+1.sierra+nevada+beer+camp+electric+ray.JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2176, 'OFYff7', 'Envious', 7.5, 'Michigan pears fuel a second fermentation, providing subtle nuance between grain & fruit. A slumber on oak and local raspberries adds depth and tartness.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-OFYff7-+1.Kt2sY.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2177, 'DGhJbX', 'Equinox', 8.4, 'A creamy, pale oat ale hopped up with a huge charge of Equinox and Simcoe hops for a piney, eucalyptus, cedar, sprucey, forest blast. First brewed in 1995... brewed today in a time of change.', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-DGhJbX-+1.AceofEquinox_3.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2178, 'ebYlhO', 'Eroica', 7.4, 'A Lagunitas-ified verson of a traditional Flemish Farmhouse ale.\r\nThis is a Lagunitas-ified version of a traditional Flemish Farmouse ale, aged in red wine oak barrels and funkied up with Brettanomyces yeast. It’s a golden saison-sour with a nice tartness that leaves your buds quenched and wanting more. Proost!', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-ebYlhO-+1.maxresdefault.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2179, 'MtJRP6', 'ESB', 5.5, 'This ESB holds to its British roots. The British sweet cracker malt and bready yeast flavors are well balanced with the earthy/spicy hop profile of this beer.', 'Portsmouth Brewery', 'New Hampshire', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-MtJRP6-+1.20160208-esb-beers-vicky-wasik-4.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2180, 'TavGRG', 'ESB - Early Spring Beer', 5.9, 'From the Sierra Nevada Brewing Co. website:\r\nOur ESB combines the best of English tradition with West Coast style. A blend of malts featuring British-grown Maris Otter is balanced with the earthy spiciness of hand-selected English and US hops. The ale is left unfiltered, which enhances mouthfeel and hop aroma creating a slightly reddish-copper hue', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-TavGRG-+1.Redhook+ESB+Early+Spring+Beer.JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2181, 'LDb6oj', 'Estate Ale', 6.7, 'Here in the sun-drenched fields of California’s North Valley, the black soil is rich with promise.\r\nIn winter, rows of barley seed are laid in the freshly tilled dirt. In spring, trellises are set for hops.\r\n\r\nFrom our fields comes a remarkable homegrown ale, made with organic wet hops and barley grown at our brewery here in Chico and one of the few estate-made ales produced anywhere in the world!\r\n\r\nThis Estate Ale is rich with the flavors of the valley—featuring hops with earthy, grapefruit-like flavors and layered spicy aromas and barley with mild sweetness and smooth, toasted flavors. Together, these crops grow alongside the brewery to make a truly unique brew.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-LDb6oj-+1.Sierra%2BNevada%2BEstate%2BHomegrown%2BIPA%2B2015%2B1.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2182, 'z9eSax', 'EXPERIMENTAL HOP PILSNER', 5.5, 'We got access to two new hops that could change the way we think about adding hop flavor to pilsners. These hops, Nug-033 and Steiner 04190, reflect some of herbal and spicy character of their European predecessors, but with a new twist. Notes of lemongrass and citrus are balanced by a slight honey flavor and a smooth, chamomile-like hop aroma.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-z9eSax-+1.Sierra%2BNevada%2BExperimental%2BHop%2BPilsner.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2183, 'bTNGkO', 'Experimental Hop Session IPA', 4.6, 'Light-bodied IPAs are the perfect beers to showcase new and unique hops, and this beer doesn\'t shy away from bold hop flavor. This beer features two new hops, HBC 438 and HBC 520,which add notes of bright lemon, coconut and fresh-cut herbs in this light snappy session IPA.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-bTNGkO-+1.Sierra%2BNevada%2BExperimental%2BHop%2BSession%2BAPA.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2184, '35wxef', 'Extra Stout', 5.3, 'Complex black-hued ale with the characteristics of chocolate and coffee. One step up from a dry stout. One more reason to love Van “The Man” Morrison.', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-35wxef-+1.ges_hero_image.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2186, 'QefHZY', 'Farmhouse Hatter', 5.07, 'Farmhouse Ales were originally brewed as “Provision Beers” by farmers in Belgium and France, brewed in the winter months to be consumed during hot summer work days. They were traditionally brewed light and refreshing to aid in both hydration and energy. Wheat and Pilsner malts were used to lighten up the body of this Mad Hatter version. It was also fermented hot with a strain of Belgian Saison yeast to develop flavors of green apple, pepper and fresh cut hay. Brewed for Hatter Days!', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-QefHZY-+1.DniWc5ZXcAEK8P3.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2189, 'ePh6fw', 'Flipside Red IPA', 6.2, 'A hop-forward fix for the first days of fall\r\n\r\nJust when it feels like the dog days will never end, suddenly, the switch is flipped, the air gets cooler and it’s clear that autumn is on the way. Featuring a ruby-red hue and abundant tropical fruit and citrus hop flavors, Flipside Red IPA is the perfect beer for the final flash of summer.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-ePh6fw-+1.sierra_nevada_flipside_red_ipa_355ml_btl_large.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2190, 'OxvWPv', 'Floral IPA - Beer Camp #53', 5.9, 'This unique take on the traditional IPA style pairs with bold and intense aromas of whole-cone hop \"flowers\" with aromatic natural rose hips and petals for complex aromas and unexpected flavors.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-OxvWPv-+1.IMG_1765.JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2191, 'N5lJcK', 'Four Witches?', 7.3, 'As we kick off our Summer seasonal, Golden Cap saison, we’re excited to roll out a single-batch seasonal, “Four Witches” black saison. It’s an opportunity to explore flavor within a remarkably interpretive style. Saisons are intriguing beers as they have traditional roots, yet are a delicious forum for variation and development.  \r\n\r\nThe Four Witches art, illustrated by Kyle Bice, develops on Golden Cap’s theme, with a nod to Wizard of Oz, as L. Frank Baum wrote the book while summering in Holland, MI.  White and dark roasted wheat provide deceptively delicious body, and a playful reference to Oz’s contrast between good and wicked witches. Caramel rye and barley continue the story, along with a unique yeast character and mild spicing.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-N5lJcK-+1.ef7UH.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2192, '907FUe', 'Fugli', 5.8, 'Yuzu and Ugli fruit infusions twisted together with the blueberry, tangerine notes of Mosaic make for a tangy, juicy, zesty array of aroma and flavor. Salivation will instantly ensue with one sniff of this crushable brew (5.8% ABV, 60 IBUs) that was inspired by a Yuzu brew we made with some brewing friends in Japan.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-907FUe-+1.fugli.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2193, 'PsFAwd', 'Full Circle', 4.9, 'A kölsch-style beer, Full Circle is a refreshing celebration of our brewery’s belief in balance. The soft, well-rounded malt character, light hop profile and crisp finish bring us back around to the familiar tastes of classic, thirst quenching beer. A perfect session beer, we recommend Full Circle with fish, grilled vegetables, grilled sausages, and just about anything else served on a patio.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-PsFAwd-+1.4lWzN93.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2194, '276GV8', 'Funkytown', 6, 'Brewed with a Vienna malt base and fermented with Brettanomyces. Soured with lactobacillus in stainless vessels. Conditionned on cherries & raspberries, this beer is fhnky, malty and sour.', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-276GV8-+1.funkytown.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2195, 'w7z0LS', 'Fusion 17', 5.5, 'As you already know, this brew was designed as hybrid of WTF and Daytime with elements of Sucks thrown in, I have included a picture of how the brew progressed for those that like O.G.’s and F.G.’s. The gravity of the wort was a little higher than expected, owed to the efficiency of the brewhouse and the Daytime mash profile. Fermentation went very well and the beer finished out in about 3 days, also at a lower F.G. than expected. As a result the alcohol was indeed higher than expected, in fact the lab results just came in and our Brown Ale is 5.5% ABV. We did in fact choose Simcoe and Nelson Sauvin for the dry hop, but we also included two more of our favorites, the elusive and rare Citra and and the ever sexy Mosaic (dry hopped at 1.6 lbs/BBL). After 3 days of extraction, 2 days of cooling, and another 2 days cold stable, the beer was filtered bright last night (July 31st), and packaged this morning (August 1st). The beer is decidedly dry and drinkable, with the impressive bouquet of hop aromas and resinous kettle hop being the main event. Delicate, slightly toasted malts and a spicy rye malt backbone remain subdued, but ever present.Short version:I think as Jeremy put it on the day of recipe formulation: \"An easy drinking, hoppy brown ale.\"', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-w7z0LS-+1.Boulder_Pulp_Fusion_17-03-22_CBB_issue_19_reviews-052_8x10.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2196, 'JoGCC1', 'Fusion 18', 10, 'AN ÜBER-HOPPY IMPERIAL OATWINE', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-JoGCC1-+1.beer-lagunitas-fusion-18.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2197, 'HG1dy6', 'Fusion 21', 4.7, 'Session amber ale.', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-HG1dy6-+1.aphrodite.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2198, 'yZruL5', 'Fusion 48', 8.3, 'This beer is a HUGE un-freakin\'-filtered Oat-and-Wheat-mashed, hop-blasted Double IPA. We double dry-hopped this beast with some Loral 291, Hallertau Blanc, Citra and Galaxy hops for that extra double punch.', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-yZruL5-+1.58876530_583433802152303_1795009528737571939_n.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2200, '69R1Vd', 'G\'Knight', 8.7, 'This beer was previously know as Gordon.\r\n\r\nGordon is a hybrid version of strong ale, somewhere between an Imperial Red and a Double IPA. We make it with six different malts and three types of hops, then dry-hop it with a mutha lode of Amarillo hops.\r\n\r\nIt features a gooey, resiny aroma and a luscious mouthfeel. Gordon is brewed with dash of chocolate malt in it, to round out its load of hops and balance the beer. The result is an assertive yet exceptionally smooth version of strong beer.\r\n\r\nWe brew Gordon in tribute to the late Gordon Knight. In addition to opening some of Colorado\'s first microbreweries, Knight was a Vietnam vet, grade-A citizen, and huge promoter of craft beer. He lost his life in 2002 while fighting a wild fire outside of Lyons, Colorado.\r\n\r\nOriginally our winter seasonal beer, it has become a cult favorite of extreme-beer lovers, so we now brew occasional batches of Gordon throughout the year. Released in bottles in 2003 and 2004, Gordon is now sold in four packs of hand-labeled cans and on draft in select markets.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-69R1Vd-+1.GKNIGHT_webres.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2201, 'esFZwY', 'G\'Knight Imperial Red IPA', 8.7, 'Our ’Velvet M-80’ is a hefty, dry hopped double-red ipa with a nose full of aroma, a sticky mouthfeel, a malty middle and unctuous hop flavors. G’Knight sports a surprisingly sensuous finish for a beer of its size (8.7% ABV, 60 IBUs). It’s brewed in tribute to a fellow Colorado craft beer pioneer and Vietnam vet who died fighting a 2002 wild fire outside of our Lyons hometown. For all the details behind this tribute follow this link to www.N3978Y.com. G’Mornin’.  G’Day.  G’Knight.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-esFZwY-+1.GKNIGHT_webres.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2202, '9cqNKc', 'Georgia Brown', 5.8, 'An American Brown Ale, deep copper-colored, mild malt. Designed to be a session beer, it has a real smooth finish without a huge hop character. Smoother than a Bill Clinton apology! \r\n\r\nGold - Brown Ales Great American Beer Festival\r\n\r\nHops: Columbus, Willamette\r\nGrains: 2 Row, 70/80, Carapils, Victory, Chocolate', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-9cqNKc-+1.p1010737.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2203, 'HiunCp', 'Gingerbread Old Chub', 8, 'Old Chub with gingerbread spices.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-HiunCp-+1.OLDCHUB_webres.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2205, 'VFG5pL', 'GnarlyWine', 10.6, 'The Annual release of our BarleyWine... This is Surely Not a Beer for the Designated Driver.', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-VFG5pL-+1.Lagunitas+Olde+GnarlyWine+2011.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2206, 'jMQlvu', 'Goin\' Coastal', 6.1, 'Slide into summer and step off the grid by Goin’ Coastal with this pineapple laced IPA. The bright aromas of the five citrus hop additions are accentuated by the tropical fruit of the pineapple- and just like those three day weekends, its finish is quick.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-jMQlvu-+1.IMG_5106-Large.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2207, 'WCPtV5', 'Golden Cap Saison Ale', 6.25, 'Golden Cap Saison is a modern interpretation of a traditional farmhouse ale. A soft, pale beer, Golden Cap embodies the flavors and aromas of summer fields. Brewed with an ancestor of wheat called spelt, its straw-colored embodies the flavors and aromas of summer fields. Brewed with an ancestor of wheat called spelt, its straw-colored body, lively carbonation and a unique fermentation profile evoke fresh cut hay and cracked peppercorn.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-WCPtV5-+1.new_holland_golden_cap_saison_ale_large.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2208, 'llmv40', 'Golden IPA', 5.9, 'We’ve always had a passion for hops, but in today’s hop-heavy beer landscape it’s easy to forget where that passion came from. In the early days, one variety changed everything—the Cascade hop. It captured us then, and the flavor is still gripping: floral and grassy with a pronounced resinous pine and grapefruit aroma. Our Golden IPA pays homage to the mighty Cascade and wonderful world of hop flavor it inspired.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-llmv40-+1.organic-beer-celt-golden-ipa.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2210, 'CwbQiB', 'Grand Royal', 8.3, 'Packed to the brim with Galaxy, 007, and Mosaic hops this Double IPA is big, juicy, and completely satisfying. Notes of tropical fruit and pine are supported by a clean malt backbone.', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-CwbQiB-+1.wpid-img_40412.jpg.jpeg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2211, 'U7lF72', 'Grass Monkey', 5.4, 'Get sprung this spring with this funky monkey of a wheat ale.  A big stash of Lemondrop hops were added to the kettle and the dry hop, delivering a big citrus blast.  Lemongrass herbs were added for a refreshing twist and exotic aroma.  The light malt bill lets the piney, grassy, lemony notes shine.  Light in body with bright citrus notes, this is an extremely complex but very easy drinking brew.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-U7lF72-+1.Grass-Monkey-bottle-can.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2212, 'nPSHXY', 'Green Monsta IPA', 7.3, 'An All-American yeast teams up with Cascade, Amarillo and Centennial for a homerun of hops in every sip.', 'Wachusett Brewing Company', 'Massachusetts', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-nPSHXY-+1.Green-Monsta.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2213, 'DUmEEi', 'Green State Lager', 4.9, 'Similar to a Bohemian or Czech Pils, but adapted to the brewing conditions in Germany, producing a drier and crisper beer. Hops are present but allow the malt to shine. Get to the Green State.', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-DUmEEi-+1.GreenStateLager.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2214, 'GVNZZQ', 'Green Valley Wild Hop Lager', 5, 'Wild Hop Lager is unique and distinctive. It is made one batch at a time. It does not use any genetically modified products, pesticides or commercial fertilizers. Wild Hop Lager is made from 100% organic barley malt, certified by the USDA and the organic organization Oregon tilth.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-GVNZZQ-+1.110136_1.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2215, 'avUZok', 'Ground Score', 7.1, 'We’ve teamed up with Relix and Kyle Hollingsworth to bring you a haze-bomb of a brew: Ground Score IPA. This bad boy’s packed with El Dorado, Citra, Amarillo, and Idaho 7 hops that will sure hit your tastebuds with a hell of a lot of flavor. At a 7.1% ABV, Ground Score IPA is big, bold, and drinkable beer. Our head brewer Nick Nock describes the color as “a sunset right before the big flash,” attributing it to the malt bill of 2 Row, flaked wheat and English Premium malts. The flaked wheat gives Ground Score its blurred clarity and a nice frothy head, while the English Premium adds a slight sweetness of orange blossom honey.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-avUZok-+1.Feature-Image-01-resize.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2216, 'coUX1m', 'Gubna', 10, 'Emphasizing that complexity of character can arise from simple elements, this ale is made with three malts and one hop. Its light amber color and slightly spicy malt character are derived from the use of German Dark Munich Malt and Rye Malt respectively. North American 2-row barley combines with the other grains to lay the foundation for the hop onslaught to come. Summit hops are used exclusively in the boil for bitterness, flavor and aroma but it doesnÃ¢â?¬â?¢t end there. Post-fermentation dry hopping allows the 9.5% ABV monstrosity to gently coax the citrus rind and grapefruit aroma to join the 100 IBUs already present. This beer should greet you with a pungent citrus blast, provide a spicy yet round middle and finish with a brisk, clean bitterness.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-coUX1m-+1.8ca607d4df6fed4f6c25309d73456393.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2217, 'pq9MUi', 'Gubna Barrel Aged', 11, 'Emphasizing that complexity of character can arise from simple elements, this ale is made with three malts and one hop. Its light amber color and slightly spicy malt character are derived from the use of German Dark Munich Malt and Rye Malt respectively. North American 2-row barley combines with the other grains to lay the foundation for the hop onslaught to come. Summit hops are used exclusively in the boil for bitterness, flavor and aroma but it doesnÃ¢â?¬â?¢t end there. Post-fermentation dry hopping allows the 9.5% ABV monstrosity to gently coax the citrus rind and grapefruit aroma to join the 100 IBUs already present. This beer should greet you with a pungent citrus blast, provide a spicy yet round middle and finish with a brisk, clean bitterness.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-pq9MUi-+1.IMG-4771.JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2218, '2YWln7', 'Gubna Imperial IPA', 10, 'Each year GUBNA takes on a personality of its own. We seek out the most exciting and best available hops from each individual season to create a potent and complex Imperial IPA. GUBNA is packed with Rye and North American Pale Malt and accented with Munich Malt to give a spicy and flavorful backbone to support loads of kettle hops driving the IBUs to triple digits.\n\n** This beer will now feature different hops in the massive dry hop every year.\n\n2015 - Features whole leaf Galena hops, plus Sorachi Ace and Columbus hops.  Dry hopped with copious amounts of El Dorado, Comet and Chinook.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-2YWln7-+1.GUBNA.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2219, 'NamZiK', 'Guinness 250th Anniversary Stout', 5, 'To mark the 250 year anniversary of the signing of the lease on St. Jame\'s Gate Brewery by Arthur Guinness, we introduce a special commemorative stout. This premium recipe provides a refreshing taste, which underlies the complex flavor of stout.\r\n\r\nMade with a double brew stream that combines two types of malts, ale and stout. Carbonated. Uses Guinness yeast, triple hops and roasted barley.', 'Guinness', 'Dublin', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-NamZiK-+1.guinness250anniversary1_resized.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2220, 'Yq3v6n', 'Guinness Black Lager', 4.5, 'Guinness Black lager is a cold-brewed with roasted barley to deliver the refreshing taste of lager with the unique character of Guinness.  Enjoy ice cold straight form the bottle.', 'Guinness', 'Dublin', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Yq3v6n-+1.blacklarger_bg4_resized_1600-h.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2221, 'qbeSzR', 'Guinness Blonde', 5, 'Guinness Blonde is the first fusion beer beer in the new Guinness Discovery Series combining the best European brewing techniques with the finest American hops in a collaboration between the Guinness Master Brewers in Dublin and their US Master Brewer counterparts at the famous Latrobe Brewery in Pennsylvania.\r\n\r\nThe result is a crisp, light, but flavorful beer characteristic of the 1930\'s American Pale Lager style with just a little \'more\' hoppy and citrus characteristics and a unique biscuit malt taste that begs to be experienced.', 'Guinness', 'Dublin', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-qbeSzR-+1.blonde_bg3__resized_1600-h.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2222, 'StkEiv', 'Guinness Draught', 4.3, 'Swirling clouds tumble as the storm begins to calm, settle, breathe in the moment, then break through the smooth, light head to the bittersweet reward. Unmistakably GUINNESS® beer, stout, or draught , from the first velvet sip to the last, lingering drop. And every deep-dark satisfying mouthful in between. Pure beauty. Pure GUINNESS®.', 'Guinness', 'Dublin', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-StkEiv-+1.b020db014b68f924f85e15be35302996f49b950a_guiness-draught-stout.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2223, 'K2qBGW', 'Guinness Extra Stout', 5, 'Extra Stout is a beer like no other. The most full-flavoured of all. Singular and striking. Uniquely satisfying.\r\n\r\nBrewed with extra hops and roasted barley for a natural bite. Bitter and sweet. Refreshingly crisp taste. Always rewarding.\r\n\r\nPure beauty. Pure GUINNESS®.', 'Guinness', 'Dublin', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-K2qBGW-+1.ges_hero_image.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2224, 'J9xszw', 'Guinness Foreign Extra', 7.5, 'Foreign Extra Stout is brewed with generous hops and roasted barley for a bittersweet balance & full-flavored, natural bite. Developed over 200 years ago for global export from Ireland, the addition of extra hops ensured this Stout would arrive to its destination in perfect condition. Today, Guinness Foreign Extra Stout is enjoyed by millions of people around the world.\r\nPure beauty. Pure Guinness.', 'Guinness', 'Dublin', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-J9xszw-+1.foreignextrastout_bg4_resized_1600-h.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2225, 'c9u7Eo', 'Guinness Generous Ale', 5.6, 'Inspired by Arthur’s philanthropic legacy and devotion to generous, full-flavored beers, Guinness Generous Ale is special edition holiday beer that was developed in a traditional winter ale style, but with more body and the distinct roast for which Guinness Draught is known. With a rich amber appearance, the vanilla notes accent Guinness Generous Ale’s silky, yet vibrant taste.', 'Guinness', 'Dublin', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-c9u7Eo-+1.GUINNESS-Generous-Ale.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2226, 'Ia4uJ0', 'Guinness Milk Stout', 5, 'A full-bodied stout with a velvety mouthfeel. Bursting with aromas of roasted malt and chocolate. A hint of smokiness. Our Milk Stout combines a 250-year commitment to brewing dark beers with a determination to never stop innovating.\r\n\r\nMarrying the deep roast characteristics of Guinness Draught with lactose sugar results in a unique stout with a subtle sweetness. Slight hints of caramel toffee are balanced by a subtle bitterness. Distinctly complex and best enjoyed in the company of an old friend.', 'Guinness', 'Dublin', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Ia4uJ0-+1.Guinness-Milk-Stout-in-a-Guinness-Gravity-Glass..jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2227, 'JfC6wN', 'Guinness Red Harvest Stout', 4.1, 'This beer celebrates SAMHAIN (saw-wen), and ancient Celtic Festival to mark the end of the fall harvest. Red Harvest Stout uses lightly roasted barley & sweet Irish malt.', 'Guinness', 'Dublin', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-JfC6wN-+1.IMG_3492.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2228, '4BzAQE', 'Happy Ending', 9, 'This seasonal “Catch and Release” Imperial Stout is a dry hopped stiffy, leading to an explosive finish at 9% ABV that is guaranteed to put a smile on your face.\r\nAvailable late December thru early March, in six packs, 22oz. bombers, 15.5 and 5.2 gallon kegs. Line priced with our Festive Ale, slightly higher than SweetWater’s year round lip smackin core styles.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-4BzAQE-+1.c5ffa4ebdf8d30c6258c06b4b0fbf7f7037f1a98_sweetwater-happy-ending-imperial-stout.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2229, 'Hb6O3U', 'Happy Ending', 9, 'This seasonal “Catch and Release” Imperial Stout is a dry hopped stiffy, leading to an explosive finish at 9% ABV that is guaranteed to put a smile on your face.\r\nAvailable late December thru early March, in six packs, 22oz. bombers, 15.5 and 5.2 gallon kegs. Line priced with our Festive Ale, slightly higher than SweetWater’s year round lip smackin core styles.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Hb6O3U-+1.c5ffa4ebdf8d30c6258c06b4b0fbf7f7037f1a98_sweetwater-happy-ending-imperial-stout.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2230, 'CD9BLy', 'Harmon Killerbrew', 7.6, 'This is our Oktoberfest beer and the style varies from a lager to a scotch ale. Typically a well balanced, full bodied amber ale in the 5-6% ABV range. Please check with the brewery for this years selection.', 'Harmon Brewing Company', 'Washington', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-CD9BLy-+1.ojogzgmw9gu11.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2231, 'ztJYpI', 'Harp Lager', 5, 'The best selling premium irish import lager in the world today.  This rich, golden pilsner style lager, with a smooth, refreshing hoppy taste, is brewed the irish way, using only the finest barley and pure spring water from the Cooley Mountains of Dundalk, Ireland.', 'Guinness', 'Dublin', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-ztJYpI-+1.harp-2.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2232, 'Yzokxa', 'Harp Premium Imported Lager', 4.5, 'The best selling premium irish import lager in the world today. This rich, golden pilsner style lager, with a smooth, refreshing hoppy taste, is brewed the irish way, using only the finest barley and pure spring water from the Cooley Mountains of Dundalk, Ireland.', 'Guinness', 'Dublin', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Yzokxa-+1.harp-premium-imported-lager-132-gal-keg.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2233, 'eIZS7k', 'Harvest Ale', 6.5, 'This beer is now brewed under the name \"Sierra Nevada Northern Hemisphere Harvest\"\r\n\r\nThe cornerstone of our Harvest series is the beer that started the modern-day fresh hop ale phenomenon in America, our original Harvest Ale. \r\n\r\nCreated in 1996, Harvest Ale features Cascade and Centennial hops from the Yakima Valley in Eastern Washington. These hops are harvested and shipped as wet un-dried hops the same day they are pickedto our brewery in Chico where our brewers eagerly wait to get them into the brew kettle while their oils and resins are still at their peak.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-eIZS7k-+1.2018_HarvestAle_Featured.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2234, 'x8U1bY', 'Harvest Fresh Hop IPA - Southern Hemisphere Harvest', 6.7, 'The harvest season for hops is a painfully short window—that precious time when the hops are bursting with intense aromatics. Luckily for us, harvest comes twice a year: once in each hemisphere. Southern Hemisphere features fresh New Zealand hops that are picked, dried, and shipped to our brewery within seven days. The result is a complex beer that showcases the floral and herbal flavors and aromas of Southern Cross, Pacifica, and Motueka hops. Southern Hemisphere is part of our five-bottle Harvest series which features single hop, fresh hop, wet hop, and wild hop beers.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-x8U1bY-+1.shfr-006.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2235, 'CU1fkx', 'Harvest Newly Developed Hop IPA (2015)', 6.5, 'Our quest for unique hop flavor led us to the Yakima Valley and a handful of newly developed varietals that are so cutting edge they are known only by numbers -- 431, 472, 05256, 06300. These new hops have compelling favors of vanilla, chocolate, oak and orange, creating an IPA like we\'ve never tasted before. Drink this IPA fresh and watch for the rest of this series that explores diverse hopping methods including single hop, fresh hop, wet hop, and wild hop.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-CU1fkx-+1.sierra-harvest-singlehop-set.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2236, '0oHOZv', 'Harvest Single Hop IPA - Idaho 7 Varietal', 6.5, 'On our never-ending quest for exciting hop flavors we stumbled upon a pioneering hop grower in western Idaho working with a handful of new and interesting varietals. One of these captivating hops, Idaho 7, headlines the first of five bottles in our 2015 edition of the Harvest series. Complex fruity aromas of orange and apricot mesh with hints of black tea-like character and a pleasant fresh herbal bouquet. This IPA kicks off our 2015 series exploring diverse hopping methods: single hop, fresh hop, wet hop and wild hop.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-0oHOZv-+1.4302_1500H.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2237, 'zGsXaD', 'Harvest Single Hop Mandarina Hops', 6.5, 'Brewed with Mandarina Hops', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-zGsXaD-+1.OMNI-the-next-episode-OMNI.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2238, 'FK6HtH', 'Harvest Single Hop Yakima #291', 6.5, 'Whole-cone hops, the whole time—our philosophy since the beginning. We use hops in their purest form, and we’re fortunate to get first crack at some of the rare and exciting varietals new to brew kettles. This single-hop IPA showcases newly developed hop 291’s fruity, berry-like aromas, complex floral character and hints of pepper. This intriguing varietal kicks off our five-bottle Harvest series which features single hop, fresh hop, wet hop, and wild hop beers.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-FK6HtH-+1.sierra-harvest-singlehop-set.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2239, 'ZSCpkz', 'Harvest Wet Hop IPA - Northern Hemisphere Harvest', 6.7, 'Northern Hemisphere was the first wet hop ale and it inspired the wet hop craze here in America. Wet—undried—hops go straight from the fields into our kettles within 24 hours. Because hops are incredibly perishable, using hops wet preserves all of the precious oils and resins for a unique drinking experience as evidenced by the intense herbal green flavors and citrus-like and floral aromas. Northern Hemisphere is part of our five-bottle Harvest series which features single hop, fresh hop, wet hop, and wild hop beers.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-ZSCpkz-+1.Sierra%2BNevada%2BNorthern%2BHemisphere%2BHarvest%2BWet%2BHop%2BIPA.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2240, 'Mx9jQm', 'Harvest Wild Hop IPA - Neomexicanus Varietal', 6.5, 'A few years back, we caught wind of rogue hop heads in the Southwest who began collecting some of the wild hops they found while scrambling down hillsides near their home in New Mexico. These bizarre, multi-headed, native U.S. cones have a flavor like nothing we’ve tasted, and for the first time, we’re showcasing their unusual melon, apricot and citrus aromas and flavors in our beer. Neomexicanus is the literal wild card in our five-bottle Harvest series which features single hop, fresh hop, wet hop, and wild hop beers.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Mx9jQm-+1.4740_1500H.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2242, 'JKdiyv', 'Hash Session IPA', 4.2, 'Cooling out on the dock, jamming tunes and popping tops, wait for da rod to bend. Gist of the grist is mellow at 4.2%, laying down the base to showcase the blazin’ Amarillo hop hash sunset.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-JKdiyv-+1.Sweetwater%2BHash%2BSession%2BIPA.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2243, 'JzAHi3', 'Hatchery Series #5 - NE Style IPA', 7.5, 'This NE style IPA offers an extremely hoppy beer with restraibed bitterness and a soft mouthfeel. We added flaked rye for a bit of a dirty southern twist.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-JzAHi3-+1.myhacthery5.JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2244, 'ygnsjS', 'Hatchery Series 1 - Mosaic Hop IPA', 6.4, 'Hatchery Series #1 is an India Pale Ale exclusively featuring Mosaic hops. Expect notes of juicy orange, mango, citrus and passionfruit with a tropical and biscuity nose and drinkable 6.4% ABV.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-ygnsjS-+1.hatchery-pilot-2.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2245, 'LnzGvI', 'Hatchery Series Release #6: Golden Summer Ale', 4.8, 'This easy pounder was brewed with some of the finest Australian and New Zealand hop varietals we could find and the addition of malted oats and acidulated malt to the malt bill leaves it nice and crisp without being too watered down or bitter. Suitable for all palates, this Golden Summer Ale is well balanced with a fruity aroma and a clean delicate finish sure to leave all imbibers longing for a longer summer.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-LnzGvI-+1.snakecake_cutout.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2246, 'b601KW', 'Hazy Little Thing', 6.7, 'As brewers, we get the privilege to sample our beers straight from the tanks in all their raw glory. Some beers need a little polishing to get ready to go out into the world, while others—the hop-heavy, rowdy, crowd-pleasers—should just be left alone. We wanted to share this brewery-only treat with you, so we present this Hazy Little Thing, our unfiltered, unprocessed IPA, straight from the tanks and into the can.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-b601KW-+1.sierra-nevada-hazy-little-thing-ipa-6pack-cans_0a5e9eb5-47a4-49fc-a6a2-61e789ce9e1c_1600x.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2247, 'tuyIzW', 'Hazy Memory', 7.7, 'We\'re going a bit blurry on this nebulous release... Hazy Memory is a cloudy IPA full of oats and smooth wheatly-esque-ish-ness, packed with some of the murkiest, juiciest, turbid Loral 291, Hallertau Blanc,Galaxy, and Citra hops. It\'s a huge flavor you won\'t forget!', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-tuyIzW-+1.New-to-cans-from-Lagunitas-is-Hazy-Memory-IPA-a-delicous-unfiltered-IPA..jpeg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2248, 'QFOApS', 'Hefe Proper Ale', 4, 'Breckenridge Brewery\'s Hefe Proper is an American rendition of a classic German style, brewed with 50% wheat malt and hopped sparingly. Our Hefeweizen combines handcrafted excellence with domestic beer drink ability.', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-QFOApS-+1.hwbn-gga.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2249, 'zD2FYX', 'Hefeweizen', 4, 'This is a German-style Wheat Ale. Mit hefe (with yeast); this cloudy, classic German ale is light in body, yet big in flavor. Lots of clove and a bit of banana make for a big aromatic presence.', 'Portsmouth Brewery', 'New Hampshire', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-zD2FYX-+1.erdinger_hefe-weizen.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2250, 'FW35fB', 'High Life Light', 4.5, 'Introduced in 1994, Miller High Life Light is the low-calorie version of Miller High Life, offering the same unpretentious attitude with fewer calories.', 'Miller Brewing Company', 'Wisconsin', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-FW35fB-+1.34846.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2251, 'IDxKzR', 'High West-ified Imperial Coffee Stout', 12.2, 'Up until this brew, none of Lagunitas’ barrel-aged adventures ever made it to shelves. They’ve been super-limited draft-only releases. This time we’ve made enough to actually bottle some. The 100% barrel-aged 2015 High West-ified Coffee Stout. Ale brewed with Coffee from our friends at Petaluma Coffee & Tea, then aged in Rye Whiskey barrels from our friends at High West Distillery in Park City, Utah … barrels that held High West’s Double Rye and American Prairie Bourbon, to be exact.', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-IDxKzR-+1.Lagunitas-High-West-ified-Imperial-Stout-12-Ounce-Bottle-1.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2252, 't787n5', 'Holidale (2017)', 8.8, 'Ale aged in whiskey barrels', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-t787n5-+1._abc2017christmas6pack052417ko-hr2.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2254, '9UUKMj', 'Holiday Leftovers Ale', 7.6, 'Original Gravity: 1.085', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-9UUKMj-+1.img_3013.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2255, 'afK7hW', 'Honey Blonde', 5.2, 'Honey Blonde is a light bodied, crisp and refreshing brew. German pilsner malt and a touch of white wheat are blended with honey malt, 2-row, destrin and crystal 15. Centennial, Golding, Serling and Cascade hops provide the balance. This beer finishes cri', 'Harmon Brewing Company', 'Washington', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-afK7hW-+1.Central-Waters-Honey-Blonde-Ale.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2256, '2VR5QQ', 'Hop And Sour', 4.4, 'This zesty beer was dry-hopped with a massive amount of citrus and fruity hops for an extremely hoppy—but not bitter—exploration of flavor.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-2VR5QQ-+1.AnspachHobdayBlue_1024x1024.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2257, 'fqgLPD', 'Hop Dog Fresh Hop Pale', 5.6, 'Our award winning Fresh Hop Pale is brewed once a year after hop harvest. The addition of freshly harvested hops impart a grassy hop aroma and flavor. We brew only 60 barrels per year.', 'Laughing Dog Brewing', 'Idaho', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-fqgLPD-+1.42899081_998912250299601_6419400009141190656_n.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2258, 'JOxnlJ', 'Hop Dog Harvest Pale Ale', 6.2, 'Hop Dog is a fresh Hop pale ale. Brewed once a year at harvest season, it is a Light hoppy pale ale with lots of green grassy hop notes.', 'Laughing Dog Brewing', 'Idaho', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-JOxnlJ-+1.57103405a042b83296cb0a4cdaec0055668e145e_flying-dog-pale-ale.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2259, '7HHwqy', 'Hop Hash', 7.8, 'We scraped all the hash out of the Yakima hop pelletizers we could get our sticky fingers on to concoct the dankest double IPA out there. The pure hop lupulin, aka “hash” (the resiny stuff), meshes seamlessly with the 2-row, pilsner and wheat malts, allowing it to deliver a pungent punch to the palate.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-7HHwqy-+1.hop-hash-pale-ale-india-pale-ale-caldera-brewing-beer.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2260, 'AAdvVo', 'Hop House Lager', 5, 'A crisp and full-flavoured lager with subtle malty notes and fresh hop aromas with hints of Apricot and Peach.\n\nAroma: Light and hoppy with floral and citrus notes \n\nFlavour: Full flavoured lager, hoppy with hints of peach and apricot\n\nPalate: Lively palate, crisp and refreshing taste\n\nABV: 5%\n\nAppearance: Golden amber lager with a thick frothy head', 'Guinness', 'Dublin', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-AAdvVo-+1.hophouse_bg3_resized_1600-h.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2261, 'Xmetdp', 'Hop Hunter IPA', 6.2, 'Hop Hunter IPA harnesses the complex flavors of just-picked hops through an all-new method of steam distilling wet hops before they even leave the fields. This revolutionary technique captures and intensifies the natural flavors, creating a unique and intensely aromatic beer. Our custom process gathers pure hop oil which, when combined with traditional whole-cone hops in the brew kettle and in our Hop Torpedo, makes for an incredible IPA experience.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Xmetdp-+1.sierranevada_hophunteripa.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2262, 'Pni8Jo', 'Hop Stoopid', 8, 'For those morning when you have to cut right to the chase, this is the one. Sure to blast through just about anything still lingering from the night before, this mouthful of hops and huge rich malt has a guarantee built right into the name!', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Pni8Jo-+1.lagunitas-hop-stoopid-ale.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2263, '4NgQyT', 'Hop-Scotch', 6.2, 'Peated IPA', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-4NgQyT-+1.1.-Double-Hop.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2264, 'Rj8PxJ', 'Hopfenweisse', 5.7, 'Freshly harvested Equinox hops were used in this nontraditional take on German Hefeweizen. Wheat, Munich and Vienna malts provide a refreshing base for the banana-like esters and citrus notes to dance on your palate.', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Rj8PxJ-+1.Schneider-Weisse-Sortiment-2019-web-MiRes.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2265, 'bn1wGG', 'Hopivore', 5.84, 'Hopivore features Cascade and Brewer’s Gold hops from the Leelanau Peninsula. The hot and dry weather this year helped create productive and flavorful alpha and beta acids in these maturing vines, which are in their third and fourth season.\r\n\r\nHopivore is a wet-hopped Harvest Ale, so the hops were introduced to the kettle only hours after harvest, without being dried. Hopivore presents a round, deep hop character, balanced by modestly sweet maltiness. Expect a more herbaceous hoppiness than other hop-forward beers.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-bn1wGG-+1.New%2BHolland%2BHopivore.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2266, 'qpyuqH', 'Hoppy Seconds', 8.4, 'This is our first creation of an emerging new style: An American-Style Belgian Ale. It was brewed with a true Belgian Ale yeast and fermented at a slightly warmer temperature to allow the yeast produce more fruity esters. A very basic malt bill of only 2 row and wheat was used and complimented by an obscene amount of Hersbrucker and Saaz hops. 8.4 % ABV.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-qpyuqH-+1.SecondDinner.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2267, 'XFwk42', 'Hoppy Wheat IPA', 6.2, 'An assertive hop-forward twist on wheat beer.\r\n\r\nWheat beers tend to fall on the mild and fruity end of the beer spectrum, but as hop heads, we’re turning that idea upside down by brewing a bold, hop-forward version of a wheat IPA. We’re using the light, lemony tang of wheat malt as a backdrop for layers of citrusy, grapefruit-like hop flavor from the use of whole-cone hops.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-XFwk42-+1.2e2af76a3fde8845e8cbc8f858924028.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2268, 'sAQpBR', 'Hoptimum', 9.6, 'A whole-cone hurricane of flavor.\r\n\r\nOur brewers selected the finest, most flavorful hops, pushed them beyond their limits and forged them into this all-new triple IPA. This reimagined Hoptimum is our hoppiest beer yet, providing a blend of tropical and citrus hop aroma that delivers a refined yet aggressive character.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-sAQpBR-+1.hoptimum-for-use.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2269, 'KQDQgO', 'Hoptimum', 10.4, 'A group of hop-heads and publicans challenegd our Beer Camp brewers to push the extremes of whole-cone hop brewing. The result is this: a 100 IBU, whole-cone hurrican of flavor. Simply put- Hoptimum: the biggest whole-cone IPA we have ever produced. Aggressively hopped, dry-hopped and torpedoed with our exclusive new hop varieties for ultra-intense flavors and aromas.\r\n\r\nHops, hops and more hops are the stars of this big, whole-cone Imperial IPA. Resinous ‘new-school’ and exclusive hop varieties carry the bold and aromatic nose. The flavor follows the aroma with layers of aggressive hoppiness, featuring notes of grapefruit rind, rose, lilac, cedar and tropical fruit – all culminating in a dry and lasting finish.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-KQDQgO-+1.hoptimum-for-use.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2270, 'ZRujA6', 'Hotbox Coffee IPA', 7.2, 'An odd couple can make for some of the most incredibly unique tastiness. Take Hotbox Coffee IPA (7.2% ABV, 70 IBUs) for example - a piney, citrus, mango, Simcoe-hopped IPA and an infusion of cold brew extract made with Hotbox Roasters\' Ethiopian beans poppin\' with creamy blueberry and cacao notes.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-ZRujA6-+1.PicsArt_04-19-08.27.35.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2271, 'Oobtwc', 'IceyPA', 7, 'A wheat IPA brewed in celebration of Colorado winter and Oskar Blues’ partnership with Denver’s Icelantic Skis, exclusively for the Colorado Old Chicago “I Love Beer” Mini Tour.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Oobtwc-+1.IMG_9450-(1).jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2272, 'Wemgbs', 'Imperial Black IPA', 7.3, 'Midnight and Chocolate Wheat malts create the blackness where rarely-used Zythos and Calypso hops pounce on your palate. Howie and the crew also packed American two-row, Crystal & Munich malts, Rye, Falconer\'s Flight, Simcoe, Chinook and Centennial hops into this black unfiltered masterpiece of a brew. First brewed 2012', 'Wachusett Brewing Company', 'Massachusetts', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Wemgbs-+1.Voodoo-Ranger-Black-IPA.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2273, 'CtqQJb', 'Imperial Hatter', 9.4, 'A robust renovation of the India Pale Ale. Assertive dry-hoppying provides an aromatic telltale nose, indicative of the bitter symphony to follow. Bold hop character with lively grapefruit and citrus notes.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-CtqQJb-+1.mad-hatter-lightning-sombrero-3.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2274, 'dbN8in', 'Imperial Pilsner - Beer Camp #43', 5.6, 'Packing a big hop-forward punch and bright crisp finish, this golden pilsner features a hearty dose of \"sticky\" resinous Crystal and Pacifica dry hops, which balance the light-bodied yet complex malt backbone.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-dbN8in-+1.007.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2275, 'uL3sSR', 'Imperial Pumpkin', 8, 'A generous amount of Two Row Barley is blended with Caramel Malt, Pumpkin, Belgian Candi Sugar, Vanilla, Cinnamon, Nutmeg and Ginger then fermented with our Northwest Yeast creating a profile as unique as every pumpkin in the patch.', 'Wachusett Brewing Company', 'Massachusetts', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-uL3sSR-+1.Elysian-pumpkin-lineup.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2276, 'meCiGU', 'Imperial Red Ale - Beer Camp #65', 8.1, 'This imperial Red Ale takes the intense hop profile found in a traditional double IPA and turns up the malt.  It has big aromatic hop notes of grapefruit, peach, and melon balanced by a smooth and surprisingly robust malt body.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-meCiGU-+1.Sierra+Nevada+2012+Best+of+Beer+Camp+65+Imperial+Red+Ale.JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2277, 'xdvDOQ', 'Imperial White IPA - Brewery Lane Series', 9, 'We built our new home on Brewery Lane in Littleton, Colorado, to cultivate creativity and nurture innovation. The Brewery Lane Series captures the essence of our ambition. These special hand-crafted ales are bold and adventurous.\r\n\r\nImperial White IPA offers flavors of honey, clove and banana from its Belgian yeast. Subtle wheat flavor is in harmony with lemongrass, which adds a hint of citrus. Citra and Amarillo hops impart pleasant hop flavor and aromas of tropical fruit and pine. \r\n\r\nStrong, balanced, flavorful. \r\n\r\nWelcome to Brewery Lane.', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-xdvDOQ-+1.2015_06_BMBC-2677.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2278, 'uzbisB', 'Incorrigible Reserve', 4.5, 'Michigan blueberries & blackberries fuel a second flavorful fermentation of this beer after its residence of several months in our House of Funk sour cellar', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-uzbisB-+1.C-TDo_PVwAAzRYJ.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2279, '3WxXFm', 'India Pale Ale IPA', 6.4, 'Our I.P.A. is a result of our profound love of hops and big, bold brews. A combination of Cluster, Cascade, Citra and Simcoe hops create a piney, citrus aroma and flavor.', 'Laughing Dog Brewing', 'Idaho', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-3WxXFm-+1.IMG_5651.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2280, 'si7pxG', 'IPA', 5.6, 'With an awesome floral nose and fresh hop flavor, The Purple is one of the most sessionable IPAs on the market. Beer Advocate calls it \" A damn solid American IPA\" - See more at: http://www.wachusettbrew.com/ipa.html#sthash.SchItsAb.dpuf', 'Wachusett Brewing Company', 'Massachusetts', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-si7pxG-+1.bk10400-beer.simply.beer-ipa.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2281, 'Yuzbjs', 'Irish Wheat', 5.3, 'Welcome to Ireland’s sunny side. Far away from the salty sea coastline, the Irish Midlands were the prime spot to grow the wheat for the first ever beer to use 100% Irish wheat malt. Golden in color, with a hint of spicy clove and citrus, Irish Wheat is a clean and lively wheat beer that’s perfect for any occasion.', 'Guinness', 'Dublin', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Yuzbjs-+1.guinness-irish-wheat.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2282, 'mrLL4r', 'Jack\'s Pumpkin Spice Ale', 5.5, 'Our fall seasonal is a subtle, well-balanced ale, copper in color, offering rich, full flavors and aromas of pumpkin and spices.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-mrLL4r-+1.Jacks-Pumpkin-Spice-Ale-6-pack.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2283, 'J0OjIy', 'Johnny Appleseed', 5.5, 'Johnny Appleseed Hard Cider is a refreshingly sweet and intense new drink for life’s adventures. This new hard cider is best enjoyed on the rocks to reveal its perfect balance of sweetness and intensity with a crisp and refreshing apple bite. Inspired by the legendary adventurer and storyteller, Johnny Appleseed Hard Cider was created for anyone with a story to tell. There is a bit of Johnny Appleseed in everyone who follows their own path and is inspired to discover their own adventures. So grab some friends, raise a glass and refresh your nightlife with Johnny Appleseed Hard Cider. Let the stories flow.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-J0OjIy-+1.7976c6ee-5ee3-4819-9a75-8312061bce0a_1.e3880c04d20ac84443a01222b8335cf4.jpeg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2284, 'ghPF7u', 'Juhlia', 7.2, 'Mash filtered with rye, eheat & juniper berries & fermented with a bread yeast to make this dark farmhouse ale', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-ghPF7u-+1.IMG_2706.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2285, 'xw3Nti', 'Karaoke Fail', 6.7, 'This intensely hoppy pale ale was modeled after the fruit-forward IPAs popular in the North East, with one notable exception: it\'s entirely hopped with exciting hop varietals from New Zealand including Waimea, Dr. Riding and Wai-Ito for a richly hopped brew.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-xw3Nti-+1.Co8BN0GWIAAyYLu.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2286, 'dNnIWw', 'Kate The Great Russian Imperial Stout', 9.5, 'The granddaddy of stouts.  Intended for export to the Imerial Court of Russia\'s Catherine the Great.  Jet black.  Full-bodied.  Very strong.', 'Portsmouth Brewery', 'New Hampshire', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-dNnIWw-+1.Mott-the-Lesser-beer-2019-label.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2287, 'JVv3qI', 'Kellerweis', 4.8, 'Kellerweis is one of the only American Hefeweizens made using the traditional Bavarian style of open fermentation. This difficult and labor-intensive technique adds uncommon depth and flavor complexity. Our hazy-golden hefeweizen is deeply flavorful, refreshing and perfect for a sunny day. To serve, pour two-thirds into a glass, swirl and pour the rest.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-JVv3qI-+1.sierra_nevada_kellerweis_0064.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2288, 'OIKxkJ', 'Kill Ugly Radio', 7.8, 'This Ale is Released In Celebration of the 40th Anniversary of the Release of F.Z. and The Mothers Absolutely Free', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-OIKxkJ-+1.100_7763.JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2290, 'vuZYco', 'Kolsch', 5, 'From Cologne to California, Kölsch-style beers are a favorite around the world. These light-bodied beers share the expressive character of an ale with the crisp, clean finish commonly found in lager beers. For our stamp on the style, Kölsch has a blast of floral and citrusy American and European whole-cone hops. This beer contains wheat malt to maintain the legendary drinkability of a classic Kölsch but adds a nod to our American brewing heritage and our love of hop flavor.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-vuZYco-+1.gaffel_kolsch_1.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2291, 'dWISHQ', 'Lagunator', 7.9, 'With a massive malt character, rounded out by a bitter balance from some experimental hops from the Yakima Valley, this beer will leave you saying \"I\'ll be bock!\"', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-dWISHQ-+1.DSCN1904.JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2292, 'iLlMCb', 'Lagunitas IPA', 6.2, 'This is our unique version of an ancient style. A style as old as the ocean trade routes of the last centuries Great Ships. Not as old as the equator they had to cross twice enroute, nor as old as the 10,000 or so miles of Di-Hydrogen Oxide and Sodium upon which they sailed, but older than the Circulithium-4 Lentloid that binds the Lupulin Quartnate onto your taste buds. Weird. Think about it. Now stop. OK, go again, now stop. Think again, and stop. But we digress. Made with 43 different hops and 65 various malts, this redolent ale will likely float your boat, whatever planet you\'re on.', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-iLlMCb-+1.1f2e15d928821d1327df3ee5a7284d44d84e662f_lagu-ipa.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2293, 'DwGaaX', 'Lagunitas Undercover Investigation Shut-Down Ale', 9.6, 'Our oxymoronic \'Imperial Mild\' - A redux to remember the \'05 St. Paddy\'s Day Massacre. Defiant as to style ... We Can say for sure it is unforgiven and unrepentant.', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-DwGaaX-+1.dscn3644.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2294, 'jZMQtq', 'Larry Imperial IPA', 8.5, 'We teamed up with our friends at the Publick House to create this 7.5% ABV, 85 IBU India Pale Ale, so you can enjoy it with yours.', 'Wachusett Brewing Company', 'Massachusetts', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-jZMQtq-+1.Wachusett+Larry-+Imperial+IPA.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2295, 'lj8S4n', 'Larry Triple Douple', 8.5, '\"Triple\" Double Larry is loaded with the same hop character you have grown to love, but is brewed with a traditional Belgian yeast to create a truly unique Imperial IPA', 'Wachusett Brewing Company', 'Massachusetts', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-lj8S4n-+1.WBC_Portfolio.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2296, 'Oklbuw', 'Leghorn Rye IPA', 6, 'A play on a traditional India Pale Ale, the mash for Leghorn includes three different types of rye. The rye imparts a spicy malt profile that balances the five separate hop additions. Bittered with Columbus hops and dry-hopped with Liberty, the deep hop flavor and delicate, floral boquet creates a complex, yet refreshing brew.', 'Jackalope Brewing Company', 'Tennessee', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Oklbuw-+1.bf8338a21de1c993139da5cae4f549a9b3250cff.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2298, '2NsDUk', 'Light IPA', 4, 'An easy drinking session IPA coming in at 4% ABV with 37 IBUs and only 121 calories.', 'Wachusett Brewing Company', 'Massachusetts', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-2NsDUk-+1.Best-Low-Calorie-Beers-0-Hero-1087x725.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2300, 'XDaNfi', 'Little Wolf', 4.7, 'Named for the translation of the hop plant species, “Hummulus Lupulus”, this Pale Ale was brewed with oats and features Horizon and Citra Hops.', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-XDaNfi-+1.0e6b42294cb38b4a688534a4ab01a62c.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2301, 'DqTrrP', 'Lolo IPA', 6.4, 'Lolo, a Hawaiian word for “crazy” is the perfect way to describe this dry and juicy American IPA!', 'Portsmouth Brewery', 'New Hampshire', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-DqTrrP-+1.2014_11_BMBC-8018.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2302, 'J183HL', 'London Calling', 3.2, 'English Style Session Ale', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-J183HL-+1.London-Calling.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2303, 'epip51', 'Long Steam IPA', 5.8, 'Ale brewed with rose hips and rose petals added', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-epip51-+1.Flagschip-Ale-Flasche-bearbeitet.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2304, 'zDUkcd', 'Lost Dune', 5.5, 'A refreshing and aromatic summer ale. Tropical notes of Mosaic hops and bright citrus of coriander complement the rounding smoothness of blueberries from Michigan’s dune-laden west coast.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-zDUkcd-+1.New-Holland-Lost-Dune-Blueberry-Ale.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2306, 'DNAmvo', 'LowRYEder IPA', 6.2, 'A flame throwin’ Rye IPA ignited by a 25% shot of rye malt and capped by a booty hoppin’ blast of Mt Hood and Centennial hops that makes this IPA bounce!', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-DNAmvo-+1.image2-e1421692602684.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2307, 'CWwxeR', 'Lucky 13', 8.3, 'Our 13th Anniversary Beer in was a Staff Favorite, So We Make it Each Year. BIG on the Amarillo Hops and Rich Dark Malts for a Round and Huge, Smoky Flavor.', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-CWwxeR-+1.20160425_201947.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2308, 'eEWCFd', 'Lucky U IPA', 6.2, 'We like to think this is an ale for everyone who believes you make your own luck. We sure did. And the result is a well-balanced, soulful IPA with just the right amount of hoppiness. An even keeled ale that goes down clean and refreshing, but still lets you know it’s been doted on by the Brewmaster. It\'s true to it’s IPA heritage, but also highly drinkable. Lucky U. And we seriously mean that.\r\n\r\nYeast: Top Fermented Ale Yeast\r\nMalts: Two Row Pale, Munich, Carmel, Torrified Wheat\r\nHops: Amarillo, Magnum, Perle, Cascade, Apollo, Fuggle, Goldings', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-eEWCFd-+1.LU_3.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2309, 'SItgWZ', 'Lupu Lava Tropical IPA', 6.8, 'Galaxy, Simcoe and Mosaic Hops. Mango, papaya and guava added during 2nd fermentation.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-SItgWZ-+1.Top-Beers-in-Hawaii_Aloha-Beer-Company_photo-credit-alohabeer-header.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2310, 'baONtD', 'Mad Hatter IPA', 7, 'Dry-hopping provides a distinctive and floral hop aroma, while the lively and hoppy body is subtly balanced with delicious malt notes. Hatter\'s hop character makes it a great fit for spicy dishes, bitter greens and beef.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-baONtD-+1.MadHatter-ToxtethIPA.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2311, '56hSxC', 'Madonna', 8, 'Heaps of hops! Tropical and grapefruit aroma and flavor from Citra meld beautifully with lemon-lime and nectar fruit from New Zealand Motueka. Wheat and Pilsner malt keep the body light and refreshing so the hops can express themselves.', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-56hSxC-+1.17326180-caransebes-romania-december-20-2012-bottle-of-madonna-beer-isolated-on-white.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2312, 'n8itvA', 'Maillard\'s Odyssey', 8.5, 'Maillard’s Odyssey is a robust dark ale layered with complex malt flavors of toffee, caramel, chocolate, coffee, and dark fruit. This malt-focused concept spawned a daunting grain bill featuring 10 different grains including pale malt, Munich, chocolate malt, oats, dark wheat and roasted barley for a rich, semi-sweet and intense experience.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-n8itvA-+1.bells-maillards-odyssey-beer.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2313, 'whHlqc', 'Maillard\'s Odyssey - Beer Camp Across America', 8.5, 'Rich, dark, and roasty. That was the concept Bell’s beer guru John Mallett aimed for and, true to John’s vision, Maillard’s Odyssey is exactly that. Its name honors the Maillard reaction—the “browning” of sugars and amino acids—that creates the wonderful caramelized toffee-like and roasted flavors so abundant in this beer.\r\n\r\nBell’s has done a lot to raise the Midwest’s craft beer bona fides. They are masters of many beer styles from their portfolio of top-notch American stouts all the way through to the alpha acid assault of their Hopslam Ale. Bell’s constantly reinvents beer styles and refines recipes with artful mastery and an oddball slant.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-whHlqc-+1.beercamp2014-nc-taterridge-set.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2314, 'xLOOss', 'Mama\'s Little Yella Pils', 5.3, 'Oskar Blues’ newest beer is an uncompromising, small-batch version of the beer that made Pilsen, Czech Republic famous. Unlike mass market \"pilsners\" diluted with corn & rice, Mama’s is built with 100% pale malt, German specialty malts, and Bavarian hops. While it’s rich with Czeched-out flavor, its gentle hopping (35 IBUs) and low ABV (just 5.3%) make it a luxurious but low-dose (by Oskar Blues standards) refresher.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-xLOOss-+1.MLYP_webres.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2315, 'dS0wsG', 'Mango Mosaic Pale Ale', 5.5, 'Mosaic hops naturally give off aromas of guava and mango, lending a unique sweetness to the hop character of this pale ale. To build upon the tropical attributes of the hops, we\'ve added a healthy dose of mango. Mango Mosaic Pale Ale is a well-balanced montage of fruit flavors, fresh aromas, and refreshingly crisp goodness.', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-dS0wsG-+1.Mango%20Mosaic%20Pale%20Ale%20-%20Refresh%2012oz%20BTL.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2316, 'iNpc02', 'Maple Scotch-Style Ale', 7.3, 'Scotch ales are wintertime staples, known for their rich, malty flavors with notes of caramel and toffee. This robust beer combines that traditional malt flavor with a touch of maple for an added layer of depth—perfect for sipping near a warm winter hearth.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-iNpc02-+1.maxresdefault.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2317, 'mjPDnq', 'Mash Appeal', 4.3, 'In celebration of Cleveland Beer Week, we’ve partnered with Oskar Blues Brewery and Lagerheads Brewing Company to create Mash Appeal, a Kentucky Common-style lager. Inspired by a once popular pre-prohibition style established in Louisville, Kentucky, Mash Appeal has a rich malt flavor with a tart finish.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-mjPDnq-+1.great%2Blakes%2Boskar%2Bblues%2Bmash%2Bappeal.jpeg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2318, 'fnqCGB', 'Maximus', 8.2, 'Did someone say Hops?  Caution must be exercised when drinking this beer.  It has been know to remove enamel from one\'s teeth, but fortunately it can also double as an industrial floor sealant.  Imagine our IPA on steroids.', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-fnqCGB-+1.Lagunitas_Maximus_17-05-31_CBB_Issue_20_reviews-196_6x10.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2319, '2z4qK8', 'Michigan Awesome Hatter', 5.8, 'The epitome of Hand Crafted, Michigan Awesome Hatter celebrates community, collaboration & local agriculture. Centennial hops from the Leelanau Peninsula provide bright citrusy counterpoint to the delicious and earthy malt notes from Michigan grown and malted 2-row barley. Thanks to our collaborators, Michigan Awesome.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-2z4qK8-+1.004.JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2320, 'xrpjYO', 'Mighty Brown', 7.5, 'Mighty Brown is a towering behemoth of a brown ale, rich, robust and full of personality. And it will go well with every other big event, meal or day in your life. Savor it. And ration it accordingly.\r\n\r\nYeast: California Ale\r\nMalts: Pale, Munich, Roasted Barley, Chocolate, Toasted Wheat\r\nHops: Perle, Hallertau', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-xrpjYO-+1.8Degrees-Bandit-Smoked-Brown-Ale.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2321, 'JUjEnp', 'Miller Chill', 4.1, 'Launched in 2007, Miller Chill is the only light beer brewed with a hint of lime and a pinch of salt to provide a truly refreshing beer experience. Through all of our marketing efforts, beer drinkers will see that Miller Chill is a celebration and fusion of the best of two cultures, great light beer from America and the chelada style from Mexico. It\'s the new alternative in mainstream low-cal beers ... one that provides a crisper, smoother, more refreshing beer experience.', 'Miller Brewing Company', 'Wisconsin', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-JUjEnp-+1.365434-1.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2322, 'ISlZaz', 'Miller Fortune', 6.9, 'Miller Fortune, developed to compete within spirits\' occasions, was introduced to the market in February 2014. The jet black bottle is branded with the Miller script \"M,\" a nod to Miller\'s time honored brewing tradition. Miller Fortune is undistilled at 6.9% ABV and crafted with caramel malts and cascade hops for a balanced taste and smooth finish. It\'s best served in a rocks glass.', 'Miller Brewing Company', 'Wisconsin', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-ISlZaz-+1.40394.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2323, 'Y8Ar6h', 'Miller Genuine Draft', 4.66, 'Miller Genuine Draft delivers a fresh from the tap taste through its proprietary \"cold-filtered four times\" brewing process. Introduced nationally in 1986, Miller Genuine Draft was born as the original cold-filtered packaged draft beer. Today, Miller Genuine Draft is reinforcing its status as the best draft beer in a bottle.', 'Miller Brewing Company', 'Wisconsin', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Y8Ar6h-+1.Miller-flaske.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2324, 'voS2xG', 'Miller High Life', 5, 'Miller High Life, the \"champagne of beers,\" dates to 1903. A classic American style lager, Miller High Life is known for its consistently crisp, smooth taste and iconic clear-glass bottle. Miller High Life embraces its rich heritage and is known by its drinkers as an authentic, unpretentious beer. It\'s common sense in a bottle.', 'Miller Brewing Company', 'Wisconsin', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-voS2xG-+1.719kF6HRnLL._SL1500_.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2325, 'KJIjyd', 'Miller Lite', 4.2, 'Miller Lite is the great tasting, less filling beer that created the American light beer category in 1975. Triple-hops brewed for great pilsner taste, Miller Lite is the only beer to win four gold awards in the World Beer Cup for best American-Style light lager (2006, 2002, 1998 and 1996). It also won the gold medal for best American-style Lager or Light Lager at the 2010 Great American Beer Festival.', 'Miller Brewing Company', 'Wisconsin', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-KJIjyd-+1.beer-stock-picture-3431153.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2326, 'yagN3u', 'Miller64', 2.8, 'Miller64 was introduced as the perfect choice for consumers striving to maintain a sense of healthy balance in their busy lifestyles. Combining a fresh, crisp flavor with only 64 calories and 2.4 carbohydrates, Miller64 is a guiltless pleasure for moments of relaxation.', 'Miller Brewing Company', 'Wisconsin', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-yagN3u-+1.slide_training.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2327, 'dsVALR', 'Mischievous', 5.5, 'Mischievous presents flavors derived from its 100% brettanomyces fermentation. This wild yeast contributes earthiness, spice, mineral-character and slight tartness.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-dsVALR-+1.mischievous-kea.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2328, '2FgZ04', 'Mountain Series: Salted Caramel Brown', 6.5, 'A rich, malty ale with a touch of sea salt', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-2FgZ04-+1.maxresdefault.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2329, 'YWt2Ld', 'Moving To the Country', 5, 'A perfect balance of floral and tropical hops rips through this pale ale with a sweet tartness and smooth finish that hints towards the taste of summer. The first in our Neighbor Series - this beer is Brewed in partnership with our friends at Sweetwater Brewing Company.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-YWt2Ld-+1.Braxton_Moving_to_the_Country_18-02-01_CBB_Issue-25_reviews-021_6x10.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2330, '69Yqbc', 'Mozango', 7.7, 'We\'ve got a big juicy secret for ya. Word on the street is this ale\'s loaded with bunches of earth-floral Mosaic and citrusy-piney Simcoe hops AND sources tell us it\'s even packing some fresh mango juice in the mix. Like a smooth and aromatic tropicalian punch, right in the kisser...Mozango!', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-69Yqbc-+1.hvd1tnbmott11.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2331, 'aWUHyv', 'Mozango (Fusion XXXI)', 9, 'A wheat-heavy IPA with Mosaic hops and mango juice.', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-aWUHyv-+1.Lagunitas-Mozango-Mango-Ale-Feature-1280x720.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2332, 'OPM4t8', 'Mt. Takhoma Blonde Ale', 3.8, 'German Pilsner Malt and a touch of flaked wheat are used to produce this light bodied, straw colored ale. Horizon and Glacier hops provide the balance. This beer finishes crisp and dry. Try this with and orange slice. 3.8% ABV', 'Harmon Brewing Company', 'Washington', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-OPM4t8-+1.047.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2333, 'S9QxGf', 'Myron\'s Walk - Beer Camp Across America', 5.3, 'We named this beer in honor of Myron Avery, a founder of the Appalachian Trail, or the A.T., which starts near Sierra Nevada’s North Carolina brewery and ends near Allagash’s home in Maine. Both breweries have a tremendous love of the outdoors, and Avery and the A.T. are great reminders of the wild spirit of exploration that connects us both.\r\n\r\nIn 1995, Rob Tod started Allagash Brewing Company and since then, Portland, ME, has been a place of reverence in the Belgian brewing pantheon. Allagash adds their Belgian flair to variety of beer styles and are one of the few American breweries to use a traditional coolship for true spontaneous fermentations leading to seriously complex beers native to their coastal home.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-S9QxGf-+1.20140714_002518.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2334, 'Rg6aeS', 'Narwhal', 10.2, 'A malt-forward monster, highlighting the depths of malt flavor.\r\n\r\nNarwhal Imperial Stout is inspired by the mysterious creature that thrives in deepest fathoms of the frigid Arctic Ocean. Featuring incredible depth of malt flavor, rich with notes of espresso, baker\'s cocoa, roasted grain and a light hint of smoke, Narwhal is a massive malt-forward monster. Aggressive but refined with a velvety smooth body and decadent finish, Narwhal will age in the bottle for years to come.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Rg6aeS-+1.c2cce6752258ec34883f114055a73806d68d8bcf_sierra-nevada-narwhal-stout.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2335, 'Xzoo8o', 'Natty Daddy', 8, 'Lager brewed with Natural Light’s all-natural ingredients. \r\nBrewed with: Water, Barley Malt, Cereal Grains, Hops, Yeast.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Xzoo8o-+1.175936-NATTY-DADDY-12OZ-15PK-CN.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2336, 'eI5fN2', 'New Dogtown Pale Ale', 6.2, 'This one was our first grocery store package. It is big, malty Pale Ale with a thirst-quenching hop flavor and a crispy clean finish.  WE revamped the recipe in 2008 to brighten up the hoppy kick.', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-eI5fN2-+1.lagunitas-new-dogtown_pale-ale.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2337, '3PXm6h', 'Nib Sip Chub', 7, 'American Porter with Coffee and Cocoa', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-3PXm6h-+1.OLDCHUB_webres.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2338, 'OXcz6Z', 'Nice Things IPA', 6.4, 'The boys don\' did it on this one. Hazy, hoppy, heady. They even tossed some pineapple in there. This beer\'s got hops and those things are nice. Mosaic hops run the show, featuring Amarillo and Simcoe on the chorus.\r\n\r\nBrewed with hip-hop artist (and hop hop artist -- sorry, couldn\'t resist) Chill Moody.', 'Dock Street Brewery', 'Pennsylvania', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-OXcz6Z-+1.chill+moody+nicethings+IPA.JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2339, 'sicuOa', 'Night Time', 7.9, 'Think of it like DayTime’s big, dark and scary sidekick. This ale is packed full of highly roasted malts, then counterhopped by smooth operators with the dankest, juiciest hops. Not for the lunch crowd or the faint of heart.', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-sicuOa-+1.lagunitas-night-time-ale-4.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2340, 'qVUNwf', 'Night Tripper', 10.8, 'Night Tripper is an Imperial Stout for a Fat Tuesday release. Dark, mysterious and poetic, Night Tripper\'s abundance of roasted malts, combined with flaked barley create a rich, roasty beer with deeply intense and lush flavors. Night Tripper\'s layered, nuanced tones invite intrigue and reward a curious palate.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-qVUNwf-+1.new-holland-night-tripper.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2341, 'LOVCKl', 'Night Tripper Barrel Aged', 10.8, 'Night Tripper is an Imperial Stout for a Fat Tuesday release. Dark, mysterious and poetic, Night Tripper\'s abundance of roasted malts, combined with flaked barley create a rich, roasty beer with deeply intense and lush flavors. Night Tripper\'s layered, nuanced tones invite intrigue and reward a curious palate.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-LOVCKl-+1.photo.JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2342, 'B0vbr1', 'Night Wish', 10.5, 'https://untappd.com/b/our-brewing-company-night-wish/441252', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-B0vbr1-+1.Main-Bar.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2343, 'YrOqvr', 'Nitro Irish Stout', 4.8, 'Brewed with Irish malts and roasted barley, this easy-going stout adds a welcoming Colorado spirit to a classic old world style. Dark malty flavors evolve into a notable dry character, while the nitrogen charge creates a soft pillowy head that smooths every sip. No glass? No worries. We’ve canned the cascade. Indulge in the nitro experience anywhere life takes you.', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-YrOqvr-+1.BreckNIScascade.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2344, 'ZliVSZ', 'Nitro Lucky U IPA', 5.7, 'Lucky U is a soulful IPA with just the right amount of hoppiness. Four malts and seven different hops give Lucky U IPA a well-balanced and full flavor. Nitrogen preserves those layers of interesting hop character adding a delightful, smooth mouthfeel. The transformation creates an entirely different IPA experience.\r\n\r\nNitro Luck U IPA\'s innovative packaging is nitrogen charged, producing a velvety cascading head right inside the can. This allows you to take it anywhere - drinking it from a glass or straight from the can. Enjoy your \"Nitro on the go.\"', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-ZliVSZ-+1.LU_3.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2345, 'l4L4RO', 'Nitro Series: Chocolate Orange Stout', 6, 'A twist on an American style stout, Breckenridge Brewery uses Cholaca, pure liquid cacao, and organic orange zest to offer a new way to experience traditional holiday flavors. Roasted malts compliment the chocolate and orange flavors. Mandarina Bavaria hops, a recently developed hop variety from Germany, impart subtle tangerine aromas, enhancing the citrus notes of the beer.', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-l4L4RO-+1.NCOS2_edited.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2346, 'Cwuozg', 'Nitro Vanilla Porter (NVP)', 4.7, 'Who would have thought deep in the jungles of Papua New Guinea and Madagascar grew the perfect ingredient to build an extraordinary Porter in Colorado? An ale that has all the chocolate and roasted nut flavor of a classic Porter, with an enigmatic surprise thrown in for good measure, real vanilla bean. Breckenridge Brewery’s Vanilla Porter. A vanilla kiss in a rich, dark sea.', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Cwuozg-+1.Nitro-Vanilla-Porter-16oz-Can-Image.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2347, 'TOBHd9', 'No Middle Ground', 6.9, 'At first glance, it might seem strange to combine coffee and hoppy beer, but really, the two flavors have a lot in common. Good coffee and hops both have complex and fruity aromas which create layers of flavor. No Middle Ground® is brewed with fruit-forward hop varietals and cold-brewed is added for a unique take on the IPA.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-TOBHd9-+1.DVYpqoAUQAI5wo2.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2348, 'he3yMK', 'Nooner Pilsner', 5.2, 'A crisp, hoppy take on the original session beer.\r\n\r\nGather your friends, pack the gear, and head out to wherever the day may take you. A midday go-to, Nooner is our take on the classic German-style pilsner—one of the original session beers. Nooner is easy drinking yet packed with the big flavor of spicy and floral whole-cone hops. Its brilliant golden color begs you to take a sip and sink your taste buds into an extremely welcoming beer, full of flavor and balanced by a crisp, dry finish.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-he3yMK-+1.68ebfb5fe8eccf4798dc9b634724484e3871cd4a_sierra-nevada-nooner-pilsner-web.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2349, 'zdjQs9', 'Northdown', 4.1, 'Maltier and less hoppy than an American pale ale, this English-style Best Bitter is all about balance.', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-zdjQs9-+1.8dce17c54808efe1df615cd06f265f12_original.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2350, 'WCKkkd', 'Now You Know', 6.1, 'A bitter, moderately strong American pale ale that uses its clean, supporting malt to showcase its hop character.', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-WCKkkd-+1.2fa3c4b43cf68fc6eca39f43cb67d5f8.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2351, '00CxqR', 'Nut Brown Ale', 5.2, 'Very smooth, dark brown, with a rich Belgian specialty finish.', 'Wachusett Brewing Company', 'Massachusetts', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-00CxqR-+1.nut-brown-ale1.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2352, '2EkHBG', 'NXS', 6.5, 'This “Left Coast” IPA is a collaboration between Northern California’s Sierra Nevada Brewing Co. and San Diego’s Karl Strauss Brewing Company—who together represent nearly 65 years of brewing experience. NxS is unabashedly hoppy—in true California fashion—and features hop flavors of citrus and tropical fruit with a light and crisp malt body.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-2EkHBG-+1.nxs_hero_1.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2353, 'n6p2aw', 'O\'Doul\'s', 0.5, 'O\'Doul\'s and O\'Doul\'s Amber are non-alcohol malt beverages. \r\n\r\nO’Doul’s has a mild, sweet taste with a slightly dry finish. O’Doul’s Amber has a rich, slightly sweet taste with flavorful hop finish. \r\n\r\nO’Doul’s and O’Doul’s Amber are brewed as traditional premium beers – fermented and aged to full maturity. The alcohol is then removed through the use of low temperature, low-pressure distillation. This extremely gentle process allows the alcohol to be removed without heating or cooking the beer, which retains the full, rich and delicate flavor and balance of our non-alcohol brews.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-n6p2aw-+1.42d6f214-cd8e-4ae1-8395-77ac2e02c96a_2.85161138f720da745d54faeebe270481.jpeg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2354, '4QiGHK', 'O\'Doul\'s Amber', 0.5, 'O’Doul’s has a mild, sweet taste with a slightly dry finish. O’Doul’s Amber has a rich, slightly sweet taste with flavorful hop finish. \r\n\r\nO’Doul’s and O’Doul’s Amber are brewed as traditional premium beers – fermented and aged to full maturity. The alcohol is then removed through the use of low temperature, low-pressure distillation. This extremely gentle process allows the alcohol to be removed without heating or cooking the beer, which retains the full, rich and delicate flavor and balance of our non-alcohol brews.', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-4QiGHK-+1.91jRcAm6U2L._SL1500_.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2355, 'N9aJxO', 'Oak Aged Mad Hatter India Pale Ale', 7.22, 'Mad Hatter aged in Kentucky barrels. Round, smooth wood character brings a new dimension to dry-hopped, aromatic hoppiness.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-N9aJxO-+1.325224_0_1_1.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2356, 'Jio9R0', 'Oatmeal Stout', 5, 'Rich, round and roasted, our Oatmeal Stout is satisfaction in a glass. It\'s a bold, smooth-bodied concoction that oozes dark-roasted coffee aromas and flavors of espresso and semi-sweet chocolate. We round out these heady pleasures with a dose of flaked oatmeal for a creamy body and a semi-dry finish.\r\n\r\nUnforgettable.\r\n\r\nYeast: Top Fermenting Ale Yeast\r\nMalts: Two Row Pale, Caramel, Roasted Barley, Chocolate, Oat Flakes, Black\r\nHops: Chinook, Perle', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Jio9R0-+1.20101006-oatmeal-stouts-beer-samuel-smith-vicky-wasik-5.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2357, '1HeKZM', 'Oatmeal Stout - Beer Camp #45', 9, 'This big oatmeal stout is midnight black in color-with a big, roasty, mocha-like aroma. It has a silky body from the use of rolled oats, and a round and lasting finish. Perfect as an after dinner treat', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-1HeKZM-+1.Sierra+Nevada+2012+Beer+Camp+%2345+Oatmeal+Stout.JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2358, 'qACg0q', 'Oatmeal Stout ?', 5.5, 'The addition of flaked oats adds a “smooth” texture to this big black ale. Its chocolate roasty flavors are tightened up by a well-balanced hop flavor.', 'Portsmouth Brewery', 'New Hampshire', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-qACg0q-+1.20101006-oatmeal-stouts-beer-samuel-smith-vicky-wasik-5.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2359, 'cJvlzs', 'Octoberfest', 5.2, 'We use traditional Oktoberfest specialty malts and hops to handcraft our interpretation of the style. Deep copper color with a predominant Euro-malty flavor and balanced bitterness.', 'Wachusett Brewing Company', 'Massachusetts', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-cJvlzs-+1.best-oktoberfest-beers.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2360, 'ADXvig', 'Oktober-Fiesta', 5.5, 'This is an Oktoberfest beer with a twist.  In the new world tradition for this style, Oktober-Fiesta is made with darker malts than its German counterpart.  The malts in this case are dark Caramel Munichs that give the beer a slight tang not usually found in the style.  Hops are of the Noble varieties, but take a back seat to the malt forward flavors.', 'Last Name Brewing', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-ADXvig-+1.OKTOBERFIESTA_SINGLE-768x1024.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2361, 'Pwu2fR', 'Oktoberfest', 6, 'Released each fall starting in 2015, this collaborative seasonal will feature a different German brewery every year. \r\n\r\n“We’re honored that Brauhaus Riegele, a real cornerstone of German craft brewing, is kicking off this Oktoberfest collaboration with us,” said Ken Grossman, Sierra Nevada’s founder.\r\n\r\nFamily owned like Sierra Nevada, Brauhaus Riegele has brewed excellent craft beers since 1386, and more than 600 years later, its innovation earns accolades including 2015 Craft Brewer of the Year at the Meininger International Craft Beer Awards. Just as Sierra Nevada’s Ken and Brian Grossman lead as a father-son team, Brauhaus Riegele has a father-son duo at the helm. Its 27th generation Master Brewer Dr. Sebastian Priller-Riegele works alongside his son Sebastian Priller-Riegele, a World Champion Beer Sommelier, to brew a lineup of beers that together have earned more than 200 awards and medals stateside and abroad.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Pwu2fR-+1.best-oktoberfest-beers.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2362, 'Q5y7v5', 'Oktoberfest', 6, 'We’ve partnered with Bavaria’s Weihenstephan, the world’s oldest brewery, for this American take on the classic German Oktoberfest. A malt backbone is balanced by subtle hop character in this crisp, clean, and drinkable crowd-pleaser. Nothing captures the spirit of celebration like a beer among friends.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Q5y7v5-+1.best-oktoberfest-beers.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2363, '42fXwv', 'Oktoberfest', 5.3, 'Lager', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-42fXwv-+1.best-oktoberfest-beers.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2364, 'EcAeVx', 'Oktoberfest', 6, 'We’re exploring the roots of Germany’s famous Oktoberfest beers. Each year, we partner with a different German brewer to explore a different approach to the style. This year we’re working with Bamberg, Germany’s Mahrs Bräu on a new version of the classic style. This authentic version of the festival beer is deep golden in color with a rich malt complexity, but with a noticeable spicy hop character from the use of the nearly forgotten Record hop varietal.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-EcAeVx-+1.best-oktoberfest-beers.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2365, 'sfHgoE', 'Oktoberfest', 6.2, 'Before 2014, known as Octoberfest.\r\n\r\nOctoberfest is a rich mahogany colored beer with an inviting toasted malty aroma. The beer has a medium body and a delicate sweetness with a rich nutty malt flavor. Octoberfest is made with our lager yeast and aged cold for a smoothness that eases well into a slightly dry finish and great drinkability. Come help us celebrate the transition from summer to fall with a glass of our Octoberfest and a warm autumn spirit in mind.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-sfHgoE-+1.best-oktoberfest-beers.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2366, 'KGaPva', 'Oktoberfest', 6.1, 'Each year, we partner with a different German brewer to explore the roots of Germany’s famous Oktoberfest beers. This year, we’re collaborating with Germany’s Brauhaus Miltenberger, whose approach to the classic style we’ve long admired. The result is a festival beer true to their style—deep golden in color with deceptively rich malt flavor and balanced by traditional German-grown whole-cone hops.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-KGaPva-+1.best-oktoberfest-beers.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2367, 'YUVOGh', 'Oktoberfest Marzen Lager', 5.4, 'German malts and hops along with a long lagering give this beer impeccable drinkability. The superb malt flavor is balanced by just a hint of hop bitterness. PROST!', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-YUVOGh-+1.oktoberfest-marzen-wide.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2369, 'jChDlj', 'Old Chico Crystal Wheat', 4.8, 'Old Chico Crystal Wheat is our lightest offering. This filtered beer is brewed with malted wheat and barley, and perfectly balanced by unique Crystal hops. Old Chico is a great choice for those new to craft brew and longtime beer aficionados alike—light-bodied, refreshing and wonderfully drinkable.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-jChDlj-+1.301263951-1-sierra-old-chico-crystal-wheat-12-fl-oz-s_ba959301-6299-4766-8869-8cd7a782943d.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2370, 'KmsdoV', 'Old Chub', 8, 'Old Chub is a Scottish strong ale brewed with hearty amounts of seven different malts, including crystal and chocolate malts, and a smidge of US and UK hops. Old Chub also gets a dash of beechwood-smoked grains imported from Bamburg, Germany, home of the world\'s greatest smoked beers. Old Chub is 8% alcohol by volume.  While Dale\'s satisfies our hop addiction, Old Chub takes care of our deep affections for malt.  The cola-colored beer (almost black) features a tan head, a creamy, skim-milk mouthfeel, and rich, semi-sweet flavors of caramel and chocolate throughout. The addition of smoked grains gives Old Chub a delicate kiss of smoke on the finish.  Old Chub is the beer equivalent of a lightly smoked single malt scotch, or your favorite dark chocolate. We call it Rocky Mountain Mutha\'s Milk. People who tell us defiantly, \\I don\'t drink dark beer', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-KmsdoV-+1.OLDCHUB_webres.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2371, '9bNjNs', 'Old Chub Nitro', 8, 'Just like Old Chub... but on NITRO! A brobdingnagian celebration of rich malts and smoked grains creates a smooth ?nishing character for the herculean size of this Scotch Ale (8% A.B.V./30 IBU). The ?rst American craft nitro beer in a can, Old Chub Nitro Scotch Ale takes the big, bold original favorite and adds the creamy, velvety mouth-feel that only nitro can add and makes this local Colorado nitro unique.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-9bNjNs-+1.OLDCHUB_webres.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2372, 'lFMs56', 'Old Double Bagger Barleywine', 13.2, 'Still a youngster at this point, Old Double Bagger (ODB for short) has a long life ahead of it.  At 13.2% ABV and 100 IBUs this ale will age for years and develop over time.  Look for a straight forward spicy citrus character from the exclusive use of Columbus hops and the considerable alcohol with a subdued malt background.  This is a work in progress and we look forward to seeing how it ages.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-lFMs56-+1.New-beer-in-Tacoma-Washington.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2373, 'ZQKG7N', 'One Nut', 6.1, 'A year round Classic, Full-Bodied Brown Ale Moderately Hopped with Rich Brown Tones, 6.1% ABV\r\n\r\nSold at the Oskar Blues Grill & Brew.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-ZQKG7N-+1.Beercans-006.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2374, 'r4I50V', 'Ophelia', 6.6, 'Subtle hints of citrus round out the complex aroma of Mosaic hops, for a beer so drinkable, it’ll last through multiple acts.', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-r4I50V-+1.Ophelia6Pack.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2375, 'qQPhVI', 'Oskar Blues IPA', 6.43, 'A Metamodern IPA conceived of hand selected hops from down under. Malt barley and red wheat combine to create a clean malt backbone with foolproof flavor and mouthfeel to support the main act of Enigma, Vic Secret, Ella, Topaz and Galaxy hops. The hops strum juicy and sweet aromas with headline notes of passion fruit, raspberries, pineapple and citrus. This straight-up strain is Oskar Blues IPA (6.43% ABV). To each their own til we go home.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-qQPhVI-+1.COB_CanPic_Trop.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2376, 'UZD25d', 'Otra Vez', 4.5, 'We wanted to make one of the easiest drinking craft beers out there, and funny enough Otra Vez has been a bear to get just right,” said Ken Grossman, Sierra Nevada’s founder. “We brewed several test batches a week for nearly a year, and even delicate changes made a big difference. Then it all clicked with perfect balance and complexity. We think folks will really enjoy it.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-UZD25d-+1.Sierra_Nevada_Otra_Vez_with_Lime_Agave__11069.1530582027.1280.1280.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2377, 'cByN2F', 'Otra Vez Gose With Lime & Agave', 4.9, 'We combined the classic flavors of lime and blue agave nectar in a tart gose-style beer for the ultimate answer to the heavy heat of the day. The bright lime flavor helps wake up the palate while the mild sweetness of the agave rounds out the tangy zip of the citrus fruit. Light and refreshing, this all-new Otra Vez will have you calling for another round.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-cByN2F-+1.Sierra_Nevada_Otra_Vez_with_Lime_Agave__11069.1530582027.1280.1280.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2378, 'dM2XzJ', 'Ovila Abbey Aged Dubbel', 8.5, 'This Abbey Dubbel was aged in a blend of red wine and bourbon barrels to add a new level of complexity to an already beguiling brew. Rich malt flavors of burnt sugar and caramel blend seamlessly with bright fruit notes from the wine barrels, while the bourbon oak lends a mellow hint of vanilla.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-dM2XzJ-+1.sierranevadaovila__52427.1436935203.JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2379, 'uXdZle', 'Ovila Abbey Brown Ale (With Mandarins and Cocoa)', 7, 'In Europe, the combination of chocolate and orange has been a traditional mix for generations. Belgian-style brown ales naturally feature hints of chocolate, but this twist on the style is accented by the use of cocoa and abbey-grown mandarins for an updated interpretation of the classic pairing.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-uXdZle-+1.IMG_1762_1_1200x1600.JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2380, 'Dwhny1', 'Ovila Abbey Quad with Plums', 10.2, 'Rich, dark, and infused with the complex sweetness of abbey-grown plums.\r\n\r\nOvila Abbey Quad is heady with aromas of caramel, rich malt, and dark fruit balanced by the spiciness and delicate fruity notes of a traditional Belgian yeast. This complex beer is a collaboration between Sierra Nevada Brewing Co. and the monks of the Abbey of New Clairvaux. It features sugar plums grown on the grounds of the Abbey and harvested by the monks in Vina. We hope you enjoy this collaboration ale.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Dwhny1-+1.p1090856.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2381, '7i1hXo', 'Ovila Abbey Saison', 7.5, 'Complex yet rustic farmhouse ale.\r\n\r\nAn homage to the monks’ noble work, this unique farmhouse ale is incredibly complex with notes of lemon, pepper, straw and herbs balanced by the tang of Mandarin oranges and a spicy kick of pepper. The Mandarin oranges used to make this beer were locally grown, including a portion grown on the grounds of the Abbey of New Clairvaux and picked by hand by the community of monks living there. We hope you enjoy this collaboration ale.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-7i1hXo-+1.d18b80a827c8dcf2bcc898e1963fb0b2fe4db58c_sierra-saison.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2382, 'ONdtij', 'Ovila Abbey Saison (w/ Mandarin Oranges and Peppercorns)', 7.5, 'An homage to the monks’ noble work, this unique farmhouse ale is incredibly complex with notes of lemon, pepper, straw and herbs balanced by the tang of Mandarin oranges and a spicy kick of pepper. The Mandarin oranges used to make this beer were locally grown, including a portion grown on the grounds of the Abbey of New Clairvaux and picked by hand by the community of monks living there.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-ONdtij-+1.IMG_4582.JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2384, 'HO9ROw', 'Ovila Abbey White', 5.3, 'The monks at the Abbey of New Clairvaux hold themselves to a higher standard. So when they challenged us to create a beer that transcends all others, our brewers blended Old World tradition with modern-day mastery to deliver the perfect expression of Belgian witbier worthy of a goblet but comfortable in a pint.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-HO9ROw-+1.23668717218_83569b9540_b.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2385, 'qGQc7S', 'Ovila Belgian Golden Ale', 8.5, 'This abbey ale is a collaboration between Sierra Nevada Brewing Co. and the monks, at the Abbey of New Clairvaux. \r\n\r\nBelgian inspired golden ales are noted for their devilish personalities, but there is nothing mischievous about this complex ale. It is brilliant golden and layered with notes of summery apple and pear and pepperv spice from the use of a traditional Belgian yeast strain. \r\n\r\nA portion of proceeds from this ale goes toward the restoration of the historic Santa Maria de Ovila chapter house on the grounds of the Abbey of New Clairvaux. This medieval building stood for nearly eight centuries in Spain. William Randolph Hearst purchased the monastery 1931 and planned use the stones for a castle even grander than his famous San Simeon. Although Hearst’s, plans crumbled. these historic stones will rise again in a California Cistercian abbey.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-qGQc7S-+1.2012-07-03_23-35-02_895.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2386, 'cB7Dxt', 'Ovila Dubbel Barrel-Aged', 10.8, 'Belgian-style dubbel aged in wine barrels.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-cB7Dxt-+1.sierranevadaovila__52427.1436935203.JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2387, '4KIe0t', 'Ovila Golden With Pomegranates', 8.5, 'Pomegranates have been treasured since ancient times and used as symbols of fruitfulness and prosperity. In the modern era, they are prized for their unique sweet-tart flavor and intense red color, which acts as a perfect counterpoint for the spicy Belgian-style golden ale. This collaboration beer features pomegranates grown at the Abbey of New Clairvaux.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-4KIe0t-+1.fa1230076fd7a88a39480323347be390.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2388, 'pYkVxn', 'Pacific Daylight', 3.9, 'A lager using many of the same ingredients as a California Common Beer, but with Citra hops and a bright refreshing taste.', 'Last Name Brewing', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-pYkVxn-+1.hops-bigger-list-version.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2389, 'cdkpyx', 'Pale Ale', 5.6, 'Our most popular beer, Sierra Nevada Pale Ale, is a delightful interpretation of a classic style. It has a deep amber color and an exceptionally full-bodied, complex character. Generous quantities of premium Cascade hops give the Pale Ale its fragrant bouquet and spicy flavor.\r\n\r\n“Sierra Nevada Pale Ale is the flagship beer, the one that made Chico famous. It is a flawless beer that opens with bright, perky high notes of maltiness and orange blossom and segues into a delectable hoppiness.”', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-cdkpyx-+1.mx022_pale_ale_mixed_case.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2390, 'CZn6nT', 'Pale Ale', 5.6, 'We brew our Pale Ale “Big, Bold and Hoppy” with plenty of Cascade hops lending a floral / citrus aroma and flavor complimented with a balanced malt backbone.', 'Laughing Dog Brewing', 'Idaho', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-CZn6nT-+1.mx022_pale_ale_mixed_case.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2391, 'bnURKM', 'Paleooza', 4.4, 'Our classic Pale Ale, with Michigan grown, cascade hops and dry hopped with galaxy hops. Bright hoppiness and pleasant aromatics framed with balancing sweetness of pale malts.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-bnURKM-+1.b2c7aa8957dba56d22e6e121d8c34b92dac7d383_new-holland-paleooza.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2392, 'Tqu2Of', 'Pandora\'s Bock', 7.5, 'Desire coupled with curiosity can drive you to do many foolish things. Fortunately, opening a bottle of our Pandora’s Bock is not one of them. Once it is released, a wealth of flavor and complexity will spill out into the world. With a traditional bock flavor profile and a hint of hoppy goodness, there’s a reason it’s spoken about in mythical terms.\r\n\r\nYeast: Bavarian Lager\r\nMalts: Two Row Pale, Munich, Bonlander, Caramel\r\nHops: Strisselspalt, Chinook', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Tqu2Of-+1.8c06b267634e3e1c3e61aa43beb16168.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2393, 'gpCMad', 'Passion Blaster', 6, 'Rose ale brewed with passion fruit, raspberry, and apple.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-gpCMad-+1.DViu_xcWsAEdOf3.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2394, 'QkHinm', 'Passion Grass', 5, 'Passion Grass is brewed with both lemongrass and passion fruit. A collaboration beer between Lagunitas Brewing Company and Short’s Brewing Company.', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-QkHinm-+1.maxresdefault.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2395, 'dRGLDH', 'Peach-a-Rita', 8, 'Peach-a-Rita, please! Ripe, sweet and tart flavors you love paired with margarita flavors you love!', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-dRGLDH-+1.maxresdefault.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2396, '1yMrDb', 'Pils', 6.2, 'Our first and only lager, brewed with loads of Sax hops imported from the Czech Republic and a bottom-fermenting yeast strain that leaves it light and crisp and easy to slam, yet full of flavor and all the things you yearn for.', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-1yMrDb-+1.holsten-pils-premium-german-lager-beer-24-x-275-ml-5-abv_temp.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2397, '52gmSJ', 'Pinner Throwback IPA', 4.9, 'How do you cram as much hop & malt flavor and aroma as possible into a beer but make it crushable too? That’s the challenge we answered with PINNER Throwback IPA. This drinkable IPA uses several varieties of hops to target the ever-evolving flavor. With tropical fruits, citrus juices, pineapple and spice berry up front in the aroma and flavor, the biscuit & toasted bread at the back balance out all the hops and make a great finish to go on to your next can of PINNER. It’s the perfect beer for a little sip, sip, give.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-52gmSJ-+1.PINNER_webres.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2398, '6Q7pkn', 'Pitch-A-Tent', 9, 'Beer Camp #55\r\nAle brewed with honey & with lavender added', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-6Q7pkn-+1.b3bb42ecb552614366d6885b319e6f64.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2399, '7aZN1V', 'Plum Gose', 4.5, 'Plum', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-7aZN1V-+1.plum.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2400, 'AY6Jg8', 'Point Defiance IPA', 6.1, 'Four types of malted barley, including a specially roasted Belgium barley make up the grain bill. Centennial, Sterling, and Amarillo hops provide the big hoppy flavor. Double dry-hopped, once with raw Centennial hops and once with raw Amarillo hops present this beer\'s huge hop aroma.', 'Harmon Brewing Company', 'Washington', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-AY6Jg8-+1.be914df2ebb90ce24cfb6c31270998ef.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2401, 'hbf2am', 'Pomona Queen', 4.8, 'The starting point was a California Common, the only beer that is from our state. The end point is a refreshing amber lager, made with San Francisco lager yeast but with a less bitter and more malty flavor than its predecessor.  A beer made for an relaxing evening or any meal.', 'Last Name Brewing', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-hbf2am-+1.pomona-queen.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2402, 'cglNbC', 'Port Barrel Aged Biere De Garde', 10.2, 'Aged in tawny port barrels .... notes of stone fruit balanced with mellow toffee flavors and a smooth, round mouthfeel', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-cglNbC-+1.Cw7KUn6XcAApHwd.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2403, '0K21pW', 'Porter', 5.6, 'Dark and rich, Sierra Nevada Porter is a delicious, medium-bodied ale with a creamy head. The Porter’s smooth flavor (malty with hints of caramel) comes from a blend of deep-roasted barley malts.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-0K21pW-+1.blacksmith.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2404, 'aBYXhp', 'Porter Porter', 7.5, 'Roll up your sleeves and get to work on this deep, dark, complex beer. Named after the 18th Century luggage porters in London, it’s been a well-deserved reward for the laborer for over 200 years. We put in extra hours and doubled the wellrounded taste of a porter for our Small Batch Series. A mouthful of sweet chocolate balanced by hints of roasted coffee. This is a big beer. Job well done, folks. Job well done.\r\n\r\nYeast: Top Fermenting Ale Yeast\r\nMalts: Two Row Pale, Caramel, Chocolate, Roasted Barley and Black\r\nHops: Chinook, Palisade, Perle, Goldings', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-aBYXhp-+1.2018_Porter_Featured.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2405, 'bFMDB3', 'Portsmouth Barleywine', 11, 'With a deep amber and full-body, this intensely bold beer is made to show off the true qualities of the malts used.  Flavors of figs and dates and malt sweetness predominate with enough earthiness from the hops to make this beer well-balanced, but insanely flavorful.', 'Portsmouth Brewery', 'New Hampshire', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-bFMDB3-+1.100_1459a.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2406, 'AWdfjO', 'Priscilla', 5.2, 'This AmeriCAN take on the Belgian Classic Wit, featuring orange peel and coriander spice emanated from the basement blues music legacy Dave McIntyre (Oskar Blusologist) built at the original Oskar Blues Grill & Brew in Lyons, CO. On draft for over a decade, Priscilla\'s zesty citrus and light fresh baked bread aromas mix with spicy, fruity fermentation. Light bodied with a subtle savory spice accent and a dry, lightly tart finish you can nearly feel the flicker of the neon and sounds of the King. White Wit Wheat.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-AWdfjO-+1.maxresdefault.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2407, 'LDo4fA', 'Puff The Magic Cyser', 8.5, 'Puff the Magic Cyser is a collaborative barrel aged product between Vander Mill and New Holland Brewing Company.\r\n\r\nThis cyser is fermented with Michigan wildflower honey to complete dryness and then aged in New Holland Dragon\'s Milk barrels for 8 months.  The richness from the stout and depth of the barrel flavor make this product very complex.  A hint of the honey and acidity of the cider round out the profile.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-LDo4fA-+1.307e7e242a0e33ee866842b19c9e8254_1280x1280.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2408, 'FMWVLR', 'Puget Brown Porter', 5.6, 'Our brown porter is brewed with eight different malts to produce a smooth, well balanced, dark beer. A specially roasted barley provides a hint of chocolate. 5.6% ABV', 'Harmon Brewing Company', 'Washington', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-FMWVLR-+1.brownale.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2409, 'EbwOyu', 'Pulled Porter', 7.7, 'On the farm way too long, ol’ McDanko began showing some worrisome tendencies. Following a solid session in the hot box smoking malt, he was overcome by a methane cloud emoted from the herd. Ya heard? Reaching for the hops, he goofed and grabbed porky by the e-i-e-i-oh and plopped her in the brew kettle slow and low —that is the tempo. Knock knock —who’s them? It’s McDanko’s inbred neighbor, Geri Reynolds, swinging by delivering his deliverance with some fat back hem and some fat back them. Stepping out past some Foxy brothers picking a banjo on the porch to sample his wares, McDanko, doubled over the chopping block and squealed like a pig – wieii wieii — proclaiming this to be the most bodacious bacon beer brewed this side of the Chattoog-a!', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-EbwOyu-+1.swppbanner.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2410, 'EyM4tM', 'Pumpkin Spice Latte : Nitro Series', 5.5, 'Pumpkin Spice Latte is a stout made with dark roasted malts and carefully roasted, cold pressed coffee beans. Vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg, and cloves delicately complement the taste of rich pumpkin. These well-balanced fall flavors presented with the velvety texture of nitrogen create a truly distinctive and delicious beer.', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-EyM4tM-+1.image.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2411, 'otVuwu', 'Purebred A.P.A. Citra', 6.2, 'The first in our Purebred series of single hop A.P.A.s showcases the hop variety Citra. These are used for everything from bittering and flavor to aroma. The soft bitterness of the Citra hop makes this an extremely drinkable beer.', 'Laughing Dog Brewing', 'Idaho', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-otVuwu-+1._SC10244.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2412, 'OAko81', 'R. Prime', 6.2, 'Named in honor of famed Indian mathematician Ramanujan. The inaugural batch of this beer was a collaboration with our esteemed colleague Matt Welz. Simcoe + Citra = R’.', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-OAko81-+1.r.jpeg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2413, 's1eqWg', 'Rainy Day Blues', 6, 'Notes of chocolate, molasses, and blueberries, which are added during fermentation), and just the right amount of malty sweetness\r\n in this full-bodied Baltic Porter.', 'Jackalope Brewing Company', 'Tennessee', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-s1eqWg-+1.DqyRxAnU0AUT5sV.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2414, 'bM2eLl', 'Red Between the Lines', 6.2, 'Not your average amber ale.  A big malt beer balanced with a hefty hop bitterness.  The red color and strong malt flavor comes from dark Munich and Caramel Munich malts.  The hops are all American with three hop additions during the boil and dry hopping.  Though the strength of this beer is its malt backbone, there is a definite hop fruit flavor in the finish.', 'Last Name Brewing', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-bM2eLl-+1.20180515_180525.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2416, 'zAC6PV', 'Regal Pilsner', 7, 'All hail our Brewmaster and the fruits of his labor, Regal Pilsner.\r\n\r\nA double Pilsner with distinct hoppy attributes and a pronounced malty backbone. It is strong in character and steadfast in its resolve to provide maximum drinking pleasure. All hail our Brewmaster and the fruits of his labor, Regal Pilsner!', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-zAC6PV-+1.royal-cit-regal_2048x.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2417, 'bztkAM', 'Rhizing Bines', 8, 'On the hot side, Rhizing Bines will go through Dogfish’s signature continual-hopping process with floral and citrusy Bravo hops. On the cold side, it will be dry-hopped with an experimental varietal so new it doesn’t yet have a name, just a number: Hop 644. A component of Sierra Nevada’s aroma-boosting Torpedo system will make a pit-stop in Delaware for dry-hopping duty before it heads to Sierra’s new North Carolina brewery.\r\n\r\nTo celebrate Sierra Nevada planting East Coast roots, Dogfish Head tracked down a Carolina heirloom wheat grown and milled at Anson Mills. The soft red winter wheat contributes subtle sweet and nutty notes to this hop-forward ale.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-bztkAM-+1.Dogfish-Head-Sierra-Nevada-Life-and-Limb-Rhizing-Bines-3.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2418, '0UTcHS', 'Ripley Tripel', 9.6, 'A very effervescent, dry Belgian-style strong ale. Brewed with Belgian malt and Candi sugar. Fermented with\r\na blend of Belgian yeast and Brettanomyces to produce a complex fruity and spicy aroma and flavor.', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-0UTcHS-+1.v2suTUY.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2419, 'XlDXNh', 'River Ryed Rye IPA', 6, 'This hop-forward beer features intense citrus and herbal hop flavor balanced by the peppery spice of rye for a dry delicious end to a rafting journey.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-XlDXNh-+1.RiverRyed_12oz_Can.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2420, 'zkfPGW', 'Rompo Red Rye (Bourbon Barrel Aged)', 5.2, 'Aged in George Dickel barrel. Deer antler series', 'Jackalope Brewing Company', 'Tennessee', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-zkfPGW-+1.0cf18063a1946ae0a02a74de8e03ee6b_1280x1280.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2421, 'TLdF50', 'Rompo Red Rye Ale', 5.6, 'Named after one of the gnarliest creatures of all time, Rompo is red rye ale. The house yeast gives it a floral aroma while the flaked rye adds spice to the finish. This is our session brew and will keep you howling for more.', 'Jackalope Brewing Company', 'Tennessee', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-TLdF50-+1.BeerReview_Jackalope_RompoRedRyeAle_Hero.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2422, 'EzaTJ3', 'Runway IPA', 6.2, 'This is a true IPA, though it is at the low end for both bitterness and alcohol values. This beer has a solid malt background of 2 row and light crystal malts.  There are four additions of hops during the boil to give it the bitterness and and hop flavor that is characteristic of the style, but the thing that gives this beer its character is the generous dry hopping that fills the mouth with citrus and tropical fruit flavors.', 'Last Name Brewing', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-EzaTJ3-+1.3f34f7da5e214a8aa6297e18554112d0_1280x1280.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2423, 'qOKA1F', 'Ruthless Rye IPA', 6.6, 'Rugged and resilient, rye has been a staple grain for ages and its spicy black pepper-like flavor has been prized by distillers and brewers for centuries. Rye thrives in the harshest conditions and comes to life in Ruthless, a spicy and rugged IPA with fruity, citrus and herbal hop notes balanced with the dry spiciness of the rye, making the beer aggressive yet comforting to bolster against whatever the winter winds may bring.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-qOKA1F-+1.65a39f1e15b81c8ddeecc83ea507dadf6b4e1b87_sierra-ruthless.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2424, 'f16hLl', 'Ruthlessly Delicious', 6.2, 'A well-rounded, highly drinkable IPA. A bit of Caramel Malt barley provides the richness that mellows out the twang of the hops.', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-f16hLl-+1.urbanartifact-photobooth.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2425, 'lMlLXZ', 'Ryde Beer', 5, 'An uncommon brew that balances the unique aroma and flavor from dry-hopping with the crisp, dry finish of rye.', 'Wachusett Brewing Company', 'Massachusetts', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-lMlLXZ-+1.DSC_1037+%25282%2529.JPG');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2426, '7bnlRC', 'Rye Cocoa Porter - ScareCity #2', 10.2, 'Brewed w/ 4 types of rye malt and cocoa nib infused Belgian Candi syrup.', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-7bnlRC-+1.img_2763.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2427, 'zTJ86p', 'Rye Hatter', 6.12, 'This beer showcases it’s grain-bill, made up of rye and barley malt. The rye adds a slight spiciness to the caramel-malt base, while also creating a creamy texture. Dry-hopping contributes a fresh citrus finish.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-zTJ86p-+1.MadHatter-Redrum.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2428, 'Y6VFJW', 'Rye IPA', 6.8, 'An aggressively hopped American Style Pale Ale brewed with Simcoe and Amarillo hops. The use of 20% rye gives this ale a unique dry and spicy character.', 'Dock Street Brewery', 'Pennsylvania', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Y6VFJW-+1.RyeIPAphoto.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2429, 'mcvkTZ', 'Safari Amber', 5, 'So so', 'Anheuser-Busch InBev', 'Missouri', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-mcvkTZ-+1.IMG_2907.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2430, '4neIJi', 'Saison Dans La Maison ?', 5.6, 'This is a great representation of the style. With a diverse malt bill, Hersbrucker, and Czech Saaz hops you can enjoy all the wonderful flavors a farmhouse ale has to offer balancing hops, malt, and the earthy flavors of saison yeast.', 'Portsmouth Brewery', 'New Hampshire', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-4neIJi-+1.2016_05_BMBC-9406.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2431, 'yh28GV', 'Sakitumi', 9, 'This Raging Bull\'uva Double-ish IPA is punched with Sake Yeast and Rice, then hopped-up for a cold-clip of counter-balanced bitterness... it just don\'t mean a thing if it ain\'t got that swing!', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-yh28GV-+1.Just-an-average-quart-bottle-of-Lagunitas-Brwewing-Sakitumi-poured-into-a-BREWPUBLIC-glass..jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2432, 'CLsadV', 'Sans Souci', 5.9, 'Brewed exclusively with Pilsner malt to showcase Belgian yeast with an American hop. The yeast adds spicy notes, while El Dorado hops contribute tropical fruit and melon aromas to this light-bodied refreshing ale.', 'Zero Gravity Craft Brewery', 'Vermont', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-CLsadV-+1.1027_1500H.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2433, 'mjwrcO', 'Satellite Stout', 5.5, 'A bold roasty stout with 50lbs of organic fair trade espresso beans. A tribute to the best coffee house in town. Coffee lovers will easily embrace this delicious brew.', 'Dock Street Brewery', 'Pennsylvania', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-mjwrcO-+1.fawfwa11_xiwkmv.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2434, 'Z4LnaP', 'Second Helping IPA', 7.4, 'Sometimes a beer is more than a beer – it’s hope. Our goal with Second Helping IPA is just that. We tag-teamed this IPA, brewed with juniper berries, with our pals at The Giving Kitchen – an awesome local organization dedicated to helping folks from the hospitality industry who have hit a rough patch or experienced catastrophic emergencies.\r\n\r\nSecond Helping will be a limited release brew only available in Atlanta, and 100% of profits from the beer will be donated right back to the amazing stuff The Giving Kitchen is doing. Just one small way we can help pay it forward. For more info on what they’re all about, make sure you visit their website and check out the video below.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Z4LnaP-+1.B7QVUVWCAAA2i-V.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2435, 'LB8JzL', 'Sidecar Orange Pale Ale', 5.6, 'This beer has a pop of bright orange flavor that emphasizes the natural citrus-heavy character of Cascade, Equinox and Mandarina hops. Brewed with orange peel added directly to the kettle, and all the classic hop flavor you\'d come to expect from our all-new take on the hop-forward fruit beer.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-LB8JzL-+1.Sierra_Nevada_Sidecar_17-03-22_CBB_issue_19_reviews-047_8x10.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2436, 'GCDyUs', 'Silent Night', 11, 'Biere de Noel is a belgian style beer that is traditionally brewed during the winter months and features big malty flavors that will warm both body and spirit. Silent Night starts with a note of toffee in it’s nose, which moves on to the pallet and mingles with hints of raisin. This is a big, sweet flavored beer that will definitely take the chill away from a cold winter night.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-GCDyUs-+1.Tansey-reviews-wine-beer-spirits-large-product-image-1-406.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2437, 'dqKU6w', 'Single Hop Cascade IPA', 6.3, 'This IPA features the flavors of the Cascade hop in an all-new way. Highlighting its signature citrus, pine and floral flavors, this IPA is an homage to the hop varietal that helped cultivate the love of bold, hop-forward beers for brewers worldwide and made our original Draught-style Pale Ale a modern beer classic.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-dqKU6w-+1.GKSHP-CAS_-_Single_Hop_Cascade_Finished_Beer_-_On_Concrete.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2438, 'Mvh5U2', 'Single Hop Series: Liberty', 5, 'An American IPA made in the heart of Nashville Tennessee. This IPA is part of a series of brews dedicated to a single hop. The Liberty Hop profile shines through the whole beer.', 'Jackalope Brewing Company', 'Tennessee', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-Mvh5U2-+1.IMG_4398.jpeg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2439, 'OH98hq', 'Sinner\'s Son', 12.4, 'Bourbon barrel aged imperial coffee stout', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-OH98hq-+1.1547337330394861604658793119574.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2440, 'e0bg5f', 'Six Rights IPA -  Beer Camp', 8, 'A bitter, moderately strong American pale ale that uses it’s clean, supporting malt to showcase it’s hop character of Mosaic & Citra.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-e0bg5f-+1.beer-camp-2017.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2441, 'FlmKOv', 'Smidy', 5.2, 'This rare stout comes from a second running of the infamous Ten Fidy. Then Lactose sugar is added to make it a delicious lower ABV milk stout.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-FlmKOv-+1.8480.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2443, 'xh62VZ', 'Sneaky Pete', 10, 'Sneaky Pete is a blend of five hop types: Simcoe, Glacier, Centennial, Vanguard and Hallertuaer, with Simcoe playing the dominate role at 30%. In addition, three separate malts were used: Honey Malt, Rye Malt, and Munich Malt. The brew has a copious aroma of white grapefruit, citrus overtones, a complex rich middle and long flavors in the finish; a real beauty. Finished with wild clover honey.', 'Laughing Dog Brewing', 'Idaho', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-xh62VZ-+1.SneakyPete.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2444, 'P2rD30', 'Snow Glare', 6, 'This refreshingly soft American wheat ale with a bright burst of hops took inspiration from sunshine reflecting off melting snow during winter\'s surrender to spring. Grounded by malted wheat, Snow Glare\'s medley of Mosaic, Centennial, and Palisade hops brings tropical and floral aromas and a crisp finish. When you\'re cool with winter but also thirsty for spring, this hoppy wheat ale helps embrace the in-between.', 'Breckenridge Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-P2rD30-+1.Snow-Glare-6pk-BTL-Image.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2445, 'LPjakS', 'Snow Wit', 5.7, 'A seven-hop lineup with a Belgian twist.\r\n\r\nYou don’t need a magic mirror to see the lure of this beer. It’s brewed with seven varieties of experimental dwarf hops. These hops are so called because of their uncommon growing method—shorter hedgerows rather than tall trellis systems—that yields a denser heap of cones with unique flavors that diverge from their full-grown botanical counterparts. Each year new and different varieties are grown in this method, creating untried and exciting shifts in hop character.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-LPjakS-+1.e43f22c6d6b2acfc5129051aad888dbb.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2446, '14UQ4N', 'Snowman Stout', 5.2, 'A delicious mocha stout brewed with locally roasted cacao nibs and coffee beans, the aroma alone is enough to make us wish we could jump in the kettle on brew days. With grains including roasted barley, chocolate malt, and black malt, it will warm you\r\n up from the inside out.', 'Jackalope Brewing Company', 'Tennessee', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-14UQ4N-+1.pd3sbcv84ob01.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2447, 'NZ5gEX', 'Sour Cherry Ten FIDY', 10, 'Imperial Stout aged in oak barrel with tart pie cherries. The infamous Ten FIDY imperial stout aged for 10 months in an oak barrel with 36 pounds of tart pie cherries added after 7 months.  A slightly lactic character carouses with big alcohol, cherries and roasty-chocolate flavors.  The cherry cordial in liquid form.  10% ABV.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-NZ5gEX-+1.Ten_Fidy_1024x1024.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2448, '2ZwqMd', 'Sour Inc: Apple Rhubarb', 4.5, 'Sour Inc Apple Rhubarb Gose is kettle soured with in-house grown lactic culture. Apple and rhubarb are blended to bring the sweet and sour, then lightly salted to attain the light and crisp gose style.', 'New Holland Brewing Company', 'Michigan', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-2ZwqMd-+1.DmR9EBZXsAUatIt.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2449, '1SYQ5O', 'Southern Gothic Session Pils', 5.6, 'Southern Gothic, a 5.2 percent ABV unfiltered pilsner.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-1SYQ5O-+1.nrLFz8h.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2450, 'xXJuyA', 'Southern Hemisphere Harvest', 6.7, 'Our newest addition to our Harvest family is Southern Hemisphere Harvest. This is the first time we know of that an American brewer has put out a beer with fresh-picked hops from the southern hemisphere. The inaugural ale will debut in late April and will feature fresh Pacific Hallertau, New Zealand Motueka and New Zealand Southern Cross hops, all from New Zealand.\r\n\r\nLike our Celebration Ale, the fresh hops in this beer are dried right after being picked then shipped immediately to Chico for brewing so that they retain their peak aromatics and flavors. To ensure the freshest hops possible, we went to the added expense of flying these hops from New Zealand to Chico so we could brew with them the week after they were picked.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-xXJuyA-+1.731282-1.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2451, '7SC2N0', 'Southern Hemisphere Session IPA', 4.6, 'Citrusy, floral and sessionable, our Southern Hemisphere Session IPA is brewed with Nelson Sauvin and Wakatu hops from New Zealand, lending the beer fresh and bright aromas and flavors.', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-7SC2N0-+1.Session_2048x2048.png');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2452, '8TQNbT', 'Spinner', 5.6, 'We took our Pinner recipe and tweaked it a bit more malt and single hop Simcoe hops.', 'Oskar Blues Brewery', 'Colorado', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-8TQNbT-+1.maxresdefault.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2453, 'zJigjF', 'Spinnerbait', 6, 'The flash of this spinnerbait stimulates the senses with its sweet malty currents and deep red hues. Our BA reels with fruity esters and spicy notes from the Ardennes yeast which swirl through the Belgian rock candy, casting the perfect presentation for the hops to set the hook on this big boy.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-zJigjF-+1.bobbing-bobber-mosaic-SMaSH-spinnerbait-1030x1030.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2454, 'dODEDo', 'Spruce Beersteen', 6, 'A Black IPA, also known as a Cascadian Dark Ale, Spruce has both a powerful hop boquet,\r\n and dark, roasted caramel malts. Spruce tips are added during the brew to accent the\r\n hop aroma for this rock star of a brew.', 'Jackalope Brewing Company', 'Tennessee', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-dODEDo-+1.event-poster-4482464.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2455, 'sYYgGI', 'Squeeze Box', 6.1, 'Beer lovers who enjoyed summer’s Goin’ Coastal IPA with pineapple will be delighted by Squeeze Box’s similarities in style and drinkability, but with the seasonally appropriate update of grapefruit.', 'SweetWater Brewing Company', 'Georgia', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-sYYgGI-+1.Sweetwater%2BSqueeze%2BBox%2BIPA%2B1.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2456, 'h7N6T9', 'Stephan Urquell ?', 4, '“DID I BREW THAT?!” This Czech-style pilsner pays tribute to the famous lager style created by Josef Groll in 1842. Spicy, fresh and clean, Stephan Urquell is familiar, yet invigorating. FACT:“Urquell” is a combination of two German words that means “original source.”', 'Portsmouth Brewery', 'New Hampshire', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-h7N6T9-+1.C6u4AOeWsAAJBh7.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2457, 'qvtSfO', 'Stoopid Wit', 6, 'An Un-Freakin\'-Filtered Hoppy Belgian-ish Wit\r\nThis UNFILTERED Belgian-ish Wit-ly-esque-ish-ness brew features a dry twang of hoppy bitterness and is perfect for the summertime drinking!', 'Lagunitas Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-qvtSfO-+1.Lagunitas-Stoopid-Wit-web.jpg');
INSERT INTO `beer` VALUES (2458, 'rHCSHp', 'Stout', 5.8, 'Creamy, malty, and full-bodied, the Sierra Nevada Stout is satisfyingly rich. Caramel and Black malts give the Stout its deep, dark color and pronounced roasted flavor.\r\n\r\n“Sierra Nevada Stout is admirable from nose to finish, with notes of malty sweetness to the palate but plenty of bitterness available to set up a stimulating counterpoint.”', 'Sierra Nevada Brewing Company', 'California', 'https://beerapp2019.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/beer-rHCSHp-+1.bk10430-beer.simply.beer-stout.jpg');
